tagline: L'Ultime chapitre de la trilogie (The final chapter of the trilogy) [France]
summary: The human government develops a cure for mutations, and Jean Gray becomes a darker uncontrollable persona called the Phoenix who allies with Magneto, causing escalation into an all-out battle for the X-Men.

tagline: Out of the ashes, hope will rise.
summary: Survivors of a plane crash in the Mongolian desert work together to build a new plane.

tagline: You can never go back.
summary: When a teen is bullied, his brother and friends lure the bully into the woods to seek revenge.

tagline: They're coming.
summary: Cady Heron is a hit with The Plastics, the A-list girl clique at her new school, until she makes the mistake of falling for Aaron Samuels, the ex-boyfriend of alpha Plastic Regina George.

tagline: Based on the Pulitzer Prize winning play by David Auburn
summary: The daughter of a brilliant but mentally disturbed mathematician, recently deceased, tries to come to grips with her possible inheritance: his insanity. Complicating matters are one of her father's ex-students, who wants to search through his papers, and her estranged sister, who shows up to help settle his affairs.

tagline: The dead don't sleep.
summary: 6 months after the incidents involving the lethal videotape, new clues prove that there is a new evil lurking in the darkness.

tagline: Everyone is looking for the next big hit
summary: Disenchanted with the movie industry, Chili Palmer tries the music industry, meeting and romancing a widow of a music executive on the way.

tagline: Every nightmare has a beginning.
summary: A young programmer whose job is to watch over the reality-warping Cube defies orders to rescue an innocent mother trapped in one of its rooms.

tagline: All Speed, No Limit (U.K.)
summary: Cousins Bo, Luke, and Daisy Duke, and their uncle Jesse, egg on the authorities of Hazzard County, Boss Hogg and Sheriff Coltrane.

tagline: An adventure like you have never gnome.
summary: Separated by a garden fence and a feud, are blue gnomes on one side and red gnomes on the other. This doesn't stop blue Gnomeo and red Juliet from falling in love with each other. Do they have a future together?

tagline: Hold your breath
summary: A group of divers find themselves in deep trouble with a drug lord after they come upon the illicit cargo of a sunken airplane.

tagline: She will kill Bill
summary: The Bride continues her quest of vengeance against her former boss and lover Bill, the reclusive bouncer Budd, and the treacherous, one-eyed Elle.

tagline: Life can be a comedy or a tragedy, it all depends on how you look at it.
summary: Two alternating stories, one comedy and the other tragedy, about Melinda's attempts to straighten out her life.
A series of vignettes that all have coffee and cigarettes in common.

tagline: The closer you are to death, the harder you cling to life.
summary: The true story of two climbers and their perilous journey up the west face of Siula Grande in the Peruvian Andes in 1985.

In 1959, Truman Capote learns of the murder of a Kansas family and decides to write a book about the case. While researching for his novel In Cold Blood, Capote forms a relationship with one of the killers, Perry Smith, who is on death row.

tagline: This is one 'River' you do not want to cross.
summary: The crew of the ship Serenity try to evade an assassin sent to recapture one of their members who is telepathic.

tagline: If love is a game, who'll make the first pass?
summary: In 1925, an enterprising pro football player convinces America's too-good-to-be-true college football hero to play for his team and keep the league from going under.

In 16th century Venice, when a merchant must default on a large loan from an abused Jewish moneylender for a friend with romantic ambitions, the bitterly vengeful creditor demands a gruesome payment instead.

A comedy panel game in which being Quite Interesting is more important than being right. Sandi Toksvig is joined each week by four comedians to share anecdotes and trivia, and maybe answer some questions as well.

tagline: Every Dream Has A Beginning
summary: The extremely talented Santiago Muñez is spotted by a Newcastle United scout and given a chance at professional football.

tagline: The story of a life and everything that came after...
summary: Centers on a young girl who has been murdered and watches over her family - and her killer - from purgatory. She must weigh her desire for vengeance against her desire for her family to heal.
An adaptation of the classic Dickens tale, where an orphan meets a pickpocket on the streets of London. From there, he joins a household of boys who are trained to steal for their master.

tagline: Is it all too good to be true?
summary: A lonely mother begins receiving romantic e-mails from a secret admirer, unaware that this perfect man is really a creation of her daughter who is trying to cheer her up.

tagline: The Pawn. The Con. The Bond.
summary: After earning 00 status and a licence to kill, Secret Agent James Bond sets out on his first mission as 007. Bond must defeat a private banker funding terrorists in a high-stakes game of poker at Casino Royale, Montenegro.

tagline: What if you had a second chance with the one that got away?
summary: Nine years after Jesse and Celine first met, they encounter each other again on the French leg of Jesse's book tour.
Two disgraced FBI agents go way undercover in an effort to protect hotel heiresses the Wilson sisters from a kidnapping plot.

tagline: Time waits for one man
summary: A small-time rancher agrees to hold a captured outlaw who's awaiting a train to go to court in Yuma. A battle of wills ensues as the outlaw tries to psych out the rancher.

tagline: Ever missed the last train?
summary: Trapped in a London subway station, a woman who's being pursued by a potential attacker heads into the unknown labyrinth of tunnels beneath the city's streets.

tagline: Charlie says you let her die. (UK teaser poster)
summary: As a widower tries to piece together his life in the wake of his wife's suicide, his daughter finds solace, at first, in her imaginary friend.

tagline: So Dark The Con Of Man
summary: A murder inside the Louvre, and clues in Da Vinci paintings, lead to the discovery of a religious mystery protected by a secret society for two thousand years, which could shake the foundations of Christianity.

tagline: Some mysteries were never meant to be solved.
summary: A mother and daughter, still wounded from a bitter custody dispute, hole up in a run-down apartment building, where they are targeted by the ghost of a former resident.

tagline: A comedy with great taste.
summary: A rat who can cook makes an unusual alliance with a young kitchen worker at a famous restaurant.

tagline: Fear The Sky
summary: Deeply ensconced in a top-secret military program, three pilots struggle to bring an artificial intelligence program under control before it initiates the next world war.

tagline: Before there was Jackass, there was Dumbass.
summary: While trying to save their childhood orphanage, Moe, Larry and Curly inadvertently stumble into a murder plot and wind up starring in a reality television show.
A theatre director struggles with his work, and the women in his life, as he creates a life-size replica of New York City inside a warehouse as part of his new play.

tagline: Failure is always an Option
summary: A weekly documentary in which two Hollywood special effects experts attempt to debunk urban legends by directly testing them.

tagline: Get a clue!
summary: Bumbling Inspector Clouseau must solve the murder of a famous soccer coach and find out who stole the infamous Pink Panther diamond.

tagline: Driven by revenge...
summary: In the eighteenth century, a vampire escapes from the freak show, in which she once participated, and teams up with a group of vampire slayers to kill the man who raped her mother.

primaryTitle: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Man's Chest
originalTitle: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Man's Chest
tagline: Captain Jack is back.
summary: Jack Sparrow races to recover the heart of Davy Jones to avoid enslaving his soul to Jones' service, as other friends and foes seek the heart for their own agenda as well.
A slick young Turk kidnapped by extraterrestrials shows his great « humanitarian spirit » by outwitting the evil commander-in-chief of the planet of G.O.R.A.

tagline: At Westlakes High, There's A New Game.  Avoid Suspicion. Manipulate Your Friends. Eliminate Your Enimies.
summary: Eight unsuspecting high school seniors at a posh boarding school, who delight themselves on playing games of lies, come face-to-face with terror and learn that nobody believes a liar - even when they're telling the truth.

tagline: Welcome to Silent Hill
summary: A woman, Rose, goes in search for her adopted daughter within the confines of a strange, desolate town called Silent Hill.

tagline: One man could lead this team to glory. . . That man was busy
summary: Family man Phil Weston, a lifelong victim of his father's competitive nature, takes on the coaching duties of a kids' soccer team, and soon finds that he's also taking on his father's dysfunctional way of relating.

tagline: Dave Spritz is about to take his best shot . . . at life.
summary: A Chicago weather man, separated from his wife and children, debates whether professional and personal success are mutually exclusive.

tagline: What would You do for Power?
summary: A down-to-earth account of the lives of both illustrious and ordinary Romans set in the last days of the Roman Republic.

tagline: When every college turned them down. . . they made one up.
summary: A high school slacker who's rejected by every school he applies to opts to create his own institution of higher learning, the South Harmon Institute of Technology, on a rundown piece of property near his hometown.

tagline: Katch 'em, kill 'em
summary: Newlyweds are terrorized by demonic forces after moving into a large house that was the site of a grisly mass murder a year before.

tagline: Just think of someone you hate.
summary: A wrongfully expelled Harvard undergrad moves to London, where he is introduced to the violent underworld of football hooliganism.
A romantic police captain breaks a beautiful member of a rebel group out of prison to help her rejoin her fellows, but things are not what they seem.

tagline: He's rich, young and handsome. He's in love with you and he's your dad's boss.
summary: A middle-aged ad exec is faced with a new boss who's nearly half his age... and who also happens to be sleeping with his daughter.
After Cheryl Frasier (Heather Burns) and Stan Fields (William Shatner) are kidnapped, Gracie Hart (Sandra Bullock) goes undercover in Las Vegas, Nevada to find them.

tagline: 2 years later...
summary: An ex-mercenary is forced out of isolation when three mysterious men kidnap and brainwash the city's children afflicted with the Geostigma disease.

tagline: What else you gonna do on a Saturday?
summary: An insight on the gritty life of a bored male, Chelsea football hooligan who lives for violence, sex, drugs & alcohol.

tagline: The incredible story of the team that changed the game forever.
summary: In 1966, Texas Western coach Don Haskins led the first all-black starting line-up for a college basketball team to the NCAA national championship.

tagline: There are worlds beyond our own - the compass will show the way.
summary: In a parallel universe, young Lyra Belacqua journeys to the far North to save her best friend and other kidnapped children from terrible experiments by a mysterious organization.

tagline: The House is . . . ALIVE!
summary: Three teens discover that their neighbor's house is really a living, breathing, scary monster.
In 1950s New York, a lonely private detective afflicted with Tourette's Syndrome ventures to solve the murder of his mentor and only friend.

tagline: What seems to be the problem?
summary: A documentary comparing the highly profitable American health care industry to other nations, and HMO horror stories including shotgun deaths.

primaryTitle: Tae Guk Gi: The Brotherhood of War
summary: When two brothers are forced to fight in the Korean War, the elder decides to take the riskiest missions if it will help shield the younger from battle.

tagline: I could eat you up, I love you so.
summary: Yearning for escape and adventure, a young boy runs away from home and sails to an island filled with creatures that take him in as their king.

tagline: This Fall, adventure begins with a Z.
summary: Despite trying to keep his swashbuckling to a minimum, a threat to California's pending statehood causes the adventure-loving Don Alejandro de la Vega and his wife, Elena, to take action.

tagline: The cure for the common man.
summary: A smooth-talking man falls for a hardened columnist while helping a shy accountant woo a beautiful heiress.

tagline: A comedy for anyone whose boss is an idiot.
summary: A mockumentary on a group of typical office workers, where the workday consists of ego clashes, inappropriate behavior, and tedium.

tagline: Love. At any cost.
summary: A widower is determined to get to the bottom of a potentially explosive secret involving his wife's murder, big business, and corporate corruption.

tagline: Live it. (Season 5)
summary: Film star Vince Chase navigates the vapid terrain of Los Angeles with a close circle of friends and his trusty agent.

tagline: A therapeutic new comedy.
summary: A career driven professional from Manhattan is wooed by a young painter, who also happens to be the son of her psychoanalyst.

tagline: Death is a shortcut  (Denmark)
summary: Two strangers awaken in a room with no recollection of how they got there, and soon discover they're pawns in a deadly game perpetrated by a notorious serial killer.

tagline: This November, get a load of Chucky.
summary: Chucky and Tiffany are resurrected by their innocent gender-confused daughter, Glenda, and hit Hollywood, where a movie depicting the killer dolls' murder spree is underway.

tagline: Welcome to the private world of Jeremy and Mark - two very ordinary weirdos.
summary: Mark and Jez are a couple of twenty-something roommates who have nothing in common - except for the fact that their lives are anything but normal. Mayhem ensues as the pair strive to cope with day-to-day life.

tagline: The Future Is A No Brainer

Forgotten, he awakes five centuries in the future. He discovers a society so incredibly dumbed down that he's easily the most intelligent person alive.

tagline: From Brian de Palma director of Scarface and The Untouchables
summary: Two policemen see their personal and professional lives fall apart in the wake of the "Black Dahlia" Elizabeth Short murder investigation.
A married couple is terrorized by a series of surveillance videotapes left on their front porch.

tagline: Friends. Rivals. Sisters.
summary: Strait-laced Rose breaks off relations with her party girl sister, Maggie, over an indiscretion involving Rose's boyfriend. The chilly atmosphere is broken with the arrival of Ella, the grandmother neither sister knew existed.

tagline: Their Christmas will turn the town upside down!
summary: With their daughter, Blair, away, Luther and Nora Krank decide to skip Christmas all together until she decides to come home, causing an uproar when they have to celebrate it at the last minute.

tagline: Meet the ultimate dysfunctional family.
summary: On Christmas Eve, three homeless people living on the streets of Tokyo discover a newborn baby among the trash and set out to find its parents.

tagline: The Best In The Business Is Back In The Game.
summary: Transporter Frank Martin, surfaces in Miami, Florida and is implicated in the kidnapping of the young son of a powerful USA official.

tagline: Set sail for One Piece!
summary: Follows the adventures of Monkey D. Luffy and his pirate crew in order to find the greatest treasure ever left by the legendary Pirate, Gold Roger. The famous mystery treasure named "One Piece".

tagline: Love Is A Force Of Nature
summary: The story of a forbidden and secretive relationship between two cowboys, and their lives over the years.
In the 1913 US Open, 20-year-old Francis Ouimet played golf against his idol, 1900 US Open champion, Englishman Harry Vardon.

tagline: To fight the enemy, she must become one of them.
summary: In the Nazi-occupied Netherlands during World War II, a Jewish singer infiltrates the regional Gestapo headquarters for the Dutch resistance.

tagline: Over the past 50 years, thousands of people disappeared. This July, they're back
summary: As the reappearance of 4,400 missing persons on a single day confounds the global community, federal agents on the case slowly discover the ways in which the victims have been changed.

tagline: Welcome to Barrow (Alaska), Inhabitants: (scratched number 588') 15
summary: After an Alaskan town is plunged into darkness for a month, it is attacked by a bloodthirsty gang of vampires.

tagline: Hold onto your honey.
summary: Barry B. Benson, a bee just graduated from college, is disillusioned at his lone career choice: making honey. On a special trip outside the hive, Barry's life is saved by Vanessa, a florist in New York City. As their relationship blossoms, he discovers humans actually eat honey, and subsequently decides to sue them.

tagline: What If You Had A Universal Remote... That Controlled Your Universe?
summary: A workaholic architect finds a universal remote that allows him to fast-forward and rewind to different parts of his life. Complications arise when the remote starts to overrule his choices.

tagline: Hope comes alive on Friday nights
summary: Based on H.G. Bissinger's book, which profiled the economically depressed town of Odessa, Texas and their heroic high school football team, The Permian High Panthers.

tagline: Basada en 1000 historias reales. (Based on 1,000 true stories)
summary: A pregnant Colombian teenager becomes a drug mule to make some desperately needed money for her family.

tagline: If you always want what you can't have, what do you want when you can have anything?
summary: Four friends/fledgling entrepreneurs, knowing that there's something bigger and more innovative than the different error-checking devices they've built, wrestle over their new invention.

tagline: The first ever reality-based movie ... everything begins and ends in 30 days!
summary: While examining the influence of the fast food industry, Morgan Spurlock personally explores the consequences on his health of a diet of solely McDonald's food for one month.

tagline: Do you have a grudge?
summary: An American nurse living and working in Tokyo is exposed to a mysterious supernatural curse, one that locks a person in a powerful rage before claiming their life and spreading to another victim.

tagline: There's nothing better than a great romance... to ruin a perfectly good friendship.
summary: Unacquainted Emily and Oliver join the mile-high club together on the way from LAX to NYC--end of story. Except that they keep meeting constantly over the next seven years..

tagline: A detective story.
summary: A teenage loner pushes his way into the underworld of a high school crime ring to investigate the disappearance of his ex-girlfriend.

tagline: It begins on the street. It ends here.
summary: Controversy surrounds high school basketball coach Ken Carter after he benches his entire team for breaking their academic contract with him.

tagline: When the world closed its eyes, he opened his arms.
summary: Paul Rusesabagina, a hotel manager, houses over a thousand Tutsi refugees during their struggle against the Hutu militia in Rwanda, Africa.
After putting together another Broadway flop, down-on-his-luck producer Max Bialystock teams up with timid accountant Leo Bloom in a get-rich-quick scheme to put on the world's worst show.

tagline: This summer, go to Hell...
summary: The murderous, backwoods Firefly family take to the road to escape the vengeful Sheriff Wydell, who is not afraid of being as ruthless as his target.

tagline: This Navy S.E.A.L. Meets His Match.
summary: Having recovered from wounds received in a failed rescue operation, Navy SEAL Shane Wolfe is handed a new assignment: Protect the five Plummer kids from enemies of their recently deceased father -- a government scientist whose top-secret experiment remains in the kids' house.

tagline: New York: 8 Million People...One CSI: Team
summary: CSI head Detective Mac Taylor and his team solve crimes using forensic science in New York City.

tagline: All She Wanted Was To Make A Living. Instead She Made History.
summary: A fictionalized account of the first major successful sexual harassment case in the United States, Jenson vs. Eveleth Mines, where a woman who endured a range of abuse while working as a miner filed and won the landmark 1984 lawsuit.

primaryTitle: Perfume: The Story of a Murderer
originalTitle: Perfume: The Story of a Murderer
tagline: He lived to find beauty. He killed to possess it.
summary: Jean-Baptiste Grenouille, born with a superior olfactory sense, creates the world's finest perfume. His work, however, takes a dark turn as he searches for the ultimate scent.

tagline: They're just a couple of guys who just wanna have fun.
summary: John Beckwith and Jeremy Grey, a pair of committed womanizers who sneak into weddings to take advantage of the romantic tinge in the air, find themselves at odds with one another when John meets and falls for Claire Cleary.

tagline: If you think your family's different, wait 'til you meet the family of the future.
summary: Lewis is a brilliant inventor who meets mysterious stranger named Wilbur Robinson, whisking Lewis away in a time machine and together they team up to track down Bowler Hat Guy in a showdown that ends with an unexpected twist of fate.

tagline: You'll Learn To Love Her. Warts And All.
summary: A governess uses magic to rein in the behavior of seven ne'er-do-well children in her charge.

tagline: Prey. Slay. Display.
summary: A group of teens are unwittingly stranded near a strange wax museum and soon must fight to survive and keep from becoming the next exhibit.

tagline: Everything can change with a kiss.
summary: Manhattanite Ashley is known to many as the luckiest woman around. After a chance encounter with a down-and-out young man, however, she realizes that she's swapped her fortune for his.

tagline: Fearing Is Believing
summary: A hospice nurse working at a spooky New Orleans plantation home finds herself entangled in a mystery involving the house's dark past.

tagline: From the creator of "Family Guy" comes a man who will stop at nothing to protect his country.
summary: The random escapades of Stan Smith, a conservative C.I.A. Agent dealing with family life, and keeping America safe, all in the most absurd way possible.

tagline: The Most Amazing Story Of Survival, Friendship, And Adventure Ever Told.
summary: Brutal cold forces two Antarctic explorers to leave their team of sled dogs behind as they fend for their survival.

tagline: You're nobody until you're talked about.
summary: Privileged teens living on the Upper East Side of New York can hide no secret from the ruthless blogger who is always watching.
Nitta Sayuri reveals how she transcended her fishing-village roots and became one of Japan's most celebrated geisha.

tagline: A hero is unleashed 2008.
summary: The canine star of a fictional sci-fi/action show that believes his powers are real embarks on a cross country trek to save his co-star from a threat he believes is just as real.

tagline: Some lines should never be crossed.
summary: When two married business executives having an affair are blackmailed by a violent criminal, the two must turn the tables on him to save their families.

tagline: It's time to even the score
summary: Prison inmates form a football team to challenge the prison guards.

tagline: Get tangled up.
summary: The magically long-haired Rapunzel has spent her entire life in a tower, but now that a runaway thief has stumbled upon her, she is about to discover the world for the first time, and who she really is.

tagline: Based on a true rumor.
summary: Sarah Huttinger is a woman who learns that her family was the inspiration for the book and film "The Graduate" -- and that she just might be the offspring of the well-documented event.

tagline: Unite and fight.
summary: A police sergeant must rally the cops and prisoners together to protect themselves on New Year's Eve, just as corrupt policeman surround the station with the intent of killing all to keep their deception in the ranks.

tagline: Discover a place that will never leave you, and a friendship that will change you forever.
summary: A preteen's life turns upside down when he befriends the new girl in school and they imagine a whole new fantasy world to escape reality.

tagline: Wanna Play?
summary: The world's best fighters are invited to DOA, an invitational martial arts contest. There, four female rival fighters will have to work together to uncover the secret that the organizer of the tournament is trying to hide.

tagline: Tom Stall had the perfect life... until he became a hero.
summary: A mild-mannered man becomes a local hero through an act of violence, which sets off repercussions that will shake his family to its very core.

tagline: You have Been Chosen
summary: A man living in a futuristic sterile colony begins to question his circumscribed existence when his friend is chosen to go to the Island, the last uncontaminated place on earth.

tagline: got guns?
summary: An arms dealer confronts the morality of his work as he is being chased by an INTERPOL Agent.

tagline: He's back!
summary: Maggie Peyton, the new owner of Herbie, Number 53, the free-wheelin' Volkswagen bug with a mind of its own, puts the car through its paces on the road to becoming a NASCAR competitor.

tagline: Boyz 'n the Wood
summary: Boog, a domesticated 900lb. Grizzly bear, finds himself stranded in the woods 3 days before Open Season. Forced to rely on Elliot, a fast-talking mule deer, the two form an unlikely friendship and must quickly rally other forest animals if they are to form a rag-tag army against the hunters.

tagline: Growing up in this family, you'd have to be... C.R.A.Z.Y.
summary: A young French-Canadian, growing up in the 1960s and 1970s, struggles to reconcile his emerging homosexuality with his father's conservative values and his own Catholic beliefs.

primaryTitle: The Diving Bell and the Butterfly
tagline: Let your imagination set you free
summary: The true story of Elle editor Jean-Dominique Bauby who suffers a stroke and has to live with an almost totally paralyzed body; only his left eye isn't paralyzed.

tagline: Everything matures... eventually.
summary: A British investment broker inherits his uncle's chateau and vineyard in Provence, where he spent much of his childhood. He discovers a new laid-back lifestyle as he tries to renovate the estate to be sold.

tagline: Stories of love from the heart of the city
summary: Through the neighborhoods of Paris, love is veiled, revealed, imitated, sucked dry, reinvented and awakened.

tagline: Lost in Our World. Found in Another.
summary: Transported to Barsoom, a Civil War vet discovers a barren planet seemingly inhabited by 12-foot tall barbarians. Finding himself prisoner of these creatures, he escapes, only to encounter Woola and a princess in desperate need of a savior.

tagline: She smells like angels ought to smell.
summary: A movie that explores the dark and miserable town, Basin City, tells the story of three different people, all caught up in violent corruption.

tagline: A New Race, A New Battle, A New Hero...
summary: Picking up directly from the previous movie, vampire warrior Selene and the half werewolf Michael hunt for clues to reveal the history of their races and the war between them.

tagline: How one man betrayed the security of a nation.
summary: FBI upstart Eric O'Neill enters into a power game with his boss, Robert Hanssen, an agent who was put on trial for selling secrets to the Soviet Union.

tagline: Perfect Future Shock
summary: Aeon Flux is a mysterious assassin working for the Monicans, a group of rebels trying to overthrow the government. When she is sent on a mission to kill the Chairman, a whole new mystery is found.

tagline: Once discovered, it was changed forever
summary: The story of the English exploration of Virginia, and of the changing world and loves of Pocahontas.

tagline: Just when you thought it was safe to go back into the courtroom.
summary: Boston Legal is a spin-off of the long-running David E. Kelley series The Practice (1997), following the exploits of former Practice character Alan Shore (James Spader) at the legal firm of Crane, Poole, and Schmidt.

tagline: He won every woman's heart. She won his.
summary: The fabled romantic Giacomo Casanova, after failing to win the affection of the Venetian woman Francesca Bruni, strives to discover the real meaning of love.

tagline: Beneath heaven lies hell, beneath hell lies...
summary: Blood-thirsty creatures await a pack of divers who become trapped in an underwater cave network.

tagline: A stand off where nobody stands down.
summary: Two cops, a rookie and a grizzled vet, pursue an accomplished bank robber.

tagline: All That Stands Between Light And Darkness Is The Night Watch.
summary: A fantasy-thriller set in present-day Moscow where the respective forces that control daytime and nighttime do battle.

primaryTitle: The Sisterhood of the Traveling Pants
originalTitle: The Sisterhood of the Traveling Pants
tagline: Laugh. Cry. Share the pants.
summary: Four best girlfriends hatch a plan to stay connected with one another as their lives start off in different directions: they pass around a pair of secondhand jeans that fits each of their bodies perfectly.

tagline: The revolution begins January 8
summary: While his trailer trash parents teeter on the edge of divorce, Nick Twisp sets his sights on dream girl Sheeni Saunders, hoping that she'll be the one to take away his virginity.

tagline: Leave Normal Behind.
summary: A young Jewish American man endeavors to find the woman who saved his grandfather during World War II in a Ukrainian village, that was ultimately razed by the Nazis, with the help of an eccentric local.

tagline: What happened to Emily?
summary: A lawyer takes on a negligent homicide case involving a priest who performed an exorcism on a young girl.

The lives of two lovelorn spouses from separate marriages, a registered sex offender, and a disgraced ex-police officer intersect as they struggle to resist their vulnerabilities and temptations in suburban Massachusetts.

tagline: Ready. Aim. Run.
summary: A low-ranking thug is entrusted by his crime boss to dispose of a gun that killed corrupt cops, but things get out of control when the gun ends up in wrong hands.

tagline: Nothing is private. Nothing is sacred.
summary: In 1984 East Berlin, an agent of the secret police, conducting surveillance on a writer and his lover, finds himself becoming increasingly absorbed by their lives.

tagline: Beyond his silence, there is a past. Beyond her dreams, there is a feeling. Beyond hope, there is a memory. Beyond their journey, there is a love.
summary: A determined woman works with a hardened boxing trainer to become a professional.

tagline: Everything Is Not Going To Be OK
summary: An undercover cop in a not-too-distant future becomes involved with a dangerous new drug and begins to lose his own identity as a result.

tagline: Brains, Brawn And Beyond.
summary: Set in an era where superheroes are commonly known and accepted, young William Stronghold, the son of the Commander and Jetstream, tries to find a balance between being a normal teenager and an extraordinary being.

tagline: This is the way the world ends-Not with a whimper, but with a bang.
summary: During a three-day heat wave just before a huge 4th of July celebration, an action star stricken with amnesia meets up with a porn star who is developing her own reality TV project, and a policeman who holds the key to a vast conspiracy.

tagline: Better Late Than Never.
summary: Goaded by his buddies, a nerdy guy who's never "done the deed" only finds the pressure mounting when he meets a single mother.

tagline: A Generation Awakens.
summary: The story of six young Indians who assist an English woman to film a documentary on the freedom fighters from their past, and the events that lead them to relive the long-forgotten saga of freedom.

tagline: A new adventure from the world of Jumanji
summary: Two young brothers are drawn into an intergalactic adventure when their house is hurled through the depths of space by the magical board game they are playing.

tagline: Don't Believe Your Eyes.
summary: Violinist Sydney Wells was accidentally blinded by her sister Helen when she was five years old. She submits to a cornea transplantation, and while recovering from the operation, she realizes that she is seeing dead people.

tagline: When lives are on the line, sacrifice everything.
summary: A high school swim champion with a troubled past enrolls in the U.S. Coast Guard's "A" School, where legendary rescue swimmer Ben Randall teaches him some hard lessons about loss, love, and self-sacrifice.

tagline: Life is more than the sum of its parts.
summary: A preoperative transgender woman takes an unexpected journey when she learns that she fathered a son, now a teenage runaway hustling on the streets of New York.

tagline: This Summer, the last war on Earth won't be started by humans.
summary: An updated version of H.G Wells' seminal sci-fi classic about the an alien invasion threatening the future of humanity. The catastrophic nightmare is depicted through the eyes of one American family fighting for survival.

tagline: The fight to save humanity rages on.
summary: When an old enemy, the Cylons, resurface and obliterate the 12 colonies, the crew of the aged Galactica protect a small civilian fleet - the last of humanity - as they journey toward the fabled 13th colony, Earth.

tagline: Undercover
summary: An undercover cop and a mole in the police attempt to identify each other while infiltrating an Irish gang in South Boston.

primaryTitle: Sweeney Todd: The Demon Barber of Fleet Street
originalTitle: Sweeney Todd: The Demon Barber of Fleet Street
tagline: Never Forget. Never Forgive.
summary: The infamous story of Benjamin Barker, aka Sweeney Todd, who sets up a barber shop in London which is the basis for a sinister partnership with his fellow tenant, Mrs. Lovett.

tagline: The world was watching in 1972 as 11 Israeli athletes were murdered at the Munich Olympics. This is the story of what happened next.
summary: Based on the true story of the Black September aftermath, about the five men chosen to eliminate the ones responsible for that fateful day.

tagline: Everything He loves Is About To Be Used Against Him.
summary: A security specialist is forced into robbing the bank that he's protecting, as a bid to pay off his family's ransom.

tagline: Every Heart is a revolutionary cell
summary: Three activists cobble together a kidnapping plot after they encounter a businessman in his home.

tagline: This Fall, One passenger is taking control.............to find the truth
summary: A bereaved woman and her daughter are flying home from Berlin to America. At 30,000 feet, the child vanishes, and nobody will admit she was ever on the plane.

tagline: It seemed like a good idea... at the time
summary: A newly wed man who believes he's just gotten hitched to the perfect woman encounters another lady on his honeymoon.

tagline: She Always Thought She Was Somebody... And She Was
summary: Upon learning of a terminal illness, a shy woman decides to sell off all her possessions and live it up at a posh Central-European hotel.

tagline: SOS '06
summary: On New Year's Eve, the luxury ocean liner Poseidon capsizes after being swamped by a rogue wave. The survivors are left to fight for their lives as they attempt to escape the sinking ship.

tagline: A world at peace. There had to be sacrifice.
summary: In 1985 where former superheroes exist, the murder of a colleague sends active vigilante Rorschach into his own sprawling investigation, uncovering something that could completely change the course of history as we know it.
Naruto Uzumaki, a mischievous adolescent ninja, struggles as he searches for recognition and dreams of becoming the Hokage, the village's leader and strongest ninja.

tagline: First contact. Last stand.
summary: A spaceship arrives in Arizona, 1873, to take over the Earth, starting with the Wild West region. A posse of cowboys and natives are all that stand in their way.

tagline: First film of the year
summary: A man who serves in the war between the forces of Light and Dark comes into possession of a device that can restore life to Moscow, which was nearly destroyed by an apocalyptic event.

tagline: The music will inspire them. The dream will unite them. This summer get crunk.
summary: With help from his friends, a Memphis pimp in a mid-life crisis attempts to become a successful hip-hop emcee.

tagline: What if you found the one you were meant for... but you lived 2 years apart?
summary: A lonely doctor, who once occupied an unusual lakeside house, begins exchanging love letters with its former resident, a frustrated architect. They must try to unravel the mystery behind their extraordinary romance before it's too late.

tagline: Your adventure starts here.
summary: A young girl inhabits an isolated island with her scientist father and communicates with a reclusive author of the novel she's reading.

tagline: The squirrels made it seem less lonely
summary: Because of the actions of her irresponsible parents, a young girl is left alone on a decrepit country estate and survives inside her fantastic imagination.

tagline: Jede Frau hat ein schmutziges Geheimnis (Every women has a dirty secret)
summary: Secrets and truths unfold through the lives of female friends in one suburban neighborhood, after the mysterious suicide of a neighbor.

tagline: All of them have a secret, all of them are Lost! (UK)
summary: The survivors of a plane crash are forced to work together in order to survive on a seemingly deserted tropical island.

tagline: He has 88 minutes to solve a murder. His own.
summary: On the day that a serial killer that he helped put away is supposed to be executed, a noted forensic psychologist and college professor receives a call informing him that he has 88 minutes left to live.
The story of the notorious French gangster Jacques Mesrine, with the focus on his life and death as France's Public Enemy No. 1 in the 1970s.

tagline: From the visionary director of Pan's Labyrinth
summary: A prince of the mythical world starts a rebellion against humanity in order to rule the Earth, and Hellboy his team must fight to stop him from locating the all-powerful Golden Army.

tagline: Survival is no game.

A freelance sleuth neighbor moves Don to embark on a cross-country search for his old flames in search of answers.

tagline: The extraordinary true adventure of Burt Munro from Down Under
summary: The story of New Zealander Burt Munro, who spent years rebuilding a 1920 Indian motorcycle, which helped him set the land speed world record at Utah's Bonneville Salt Flats in 1967.

tagline: As Addictive as Vicodin (South Africa - Season 2 Tagline (2006))
summary: An antisocial maverick doctor who specializes in diagnostic medicine does whatever it takes to solve puzzling cases that come his way using his crack team of doctors and his wits.

tagline: She Sees What Others Can't.
summary: Suburban mom Allison DuBois attempts to balance family life with solving mysteries using her special gift. The dead send her visions of their deaths or other crimes while she sleeps.

tagline: Free to be Fearless
summary: After her best friend is murdered, and her father is removed as county Sheriff, Veronica Mars dedicates her life to cracking the toughest mysteries in the affluent town of Neptune.

tagline: God has a grand design... Guess who has to build it?

tagline: Cookies that talk. Trees that walk. Donkeys on deck. It must be... Shrek!
summary: Reluctantly designated as the heir to the land of Far, Far Away, Shrek hatches a plan to install the rebellious Artie as the new king while Princess Fiona tries to fend off a coup d'état by the jilted Prince Charming.

tagline: How long can any man fight the darkness... before he finds it in himself?
summary: A strange black entity from another world bonds with Peter Parker and causes inner turmoil as he contends with new villains, temptations, and revenge.

tagline: Let the healing begin.
summary: A drama centered on the personal and professional lives of five surgical interns and their supervisors.

tagline: This Christmas, help is coming from above.

tagline: Blanchett returns in the role for which she received an OSCAR nomination
summary: A mature Queen Elizabeth endures multiple crises late in her reign including court intrigues, an assassination plot, the Spanish Armada, and romantic disappointments.

tagline: Sometimes the last person on earth you want to be with is the one person you can't be without.
summary: Sparks fly when spirited Elizabeth Bennet meets single, rich, and proud Mr. Darcy. But Mr. Darcy reluctantly finds himself falling in love with a woman beneath his class. Can each overcome their own pride and prejudice?

tagline: Welcome to District B13 Welcome to the future
summary: In the ghettos of Paris in 2010, an undercover cop and an ex-thug try to infiltrate a gang in order to defuse a neutron bomb.

tagline: The Original Party Animals
summary: When the farmer's away, all the animals play, and sing, and dance. Eventually, though, someone has to step in and run things, a responsibility that ends up going to Otis, a carefree cow.

tagline: This Ride Will Be The Death Of You.
summary: Six years after students cheated death, another teen has a premonition she and her friends will be involved in an accident. When the vision proves true, the student and survivors deal with the repercussions of cheating the Grim Reaper.

tagline: Death frees every soul.
summary: As a modern-day scientist, Tommy is struggling with mortality, desperately searching for the medical breakthrough that will save the life of his cancer-stricken wife, Izzi.

primaryTitle: Talladega Nights: The Ballad of Ricky Bobby
originalTitle: Talladega Nights: The Ballad of Ricky Bobby
tagline: The story of a man who could only count to #1
summary: Number one NASCAR driver Ricky Bobby stays atop the heap thanks to a pact with his best friend and teammate, Cal Naughton, Jr. But when a French Formula One driver, makes his way up the ladder, Ricky Bobby's talent and devotion are put to the test.

primaryTitle: Me and You and Everyone We Know
originalTitle: Me and You and Everyone We Know
summary: A lonely shoe salesman and an eccentric performance artist struggle to connect in this unique take on contemporary life.

primaryTitle: Mongol: The Rise of Genghis Khan
tagline: Greatness comes to those who take it.
summary: The story recounts the early life of Genghis Khan who was a slave before going on to conquer half the world in 1206.

tagline: Their World Is Closer Than You Think
summary: Upon moving into the run-down Spiderwick Estate with their mother, twin brothers Jared and Simon Grace, along with their sister Mallory, find themselves pulled into an alternate world full of faeries and other creatures.

tagline: The Thrill Is In The Hunt.
summary: Three backpackers stranded in the Australian outback are plunged inside a hellish nightmare of insufferable torture by a sadistic psychopathic local.

tagline: Passion   Temptation  Obsession
summary: At a turning point in his life, a former tennis pro falls for an actress who happens to be dating his friend and soon-to-be brother-in-law.

tagline: Pledged to crush!
summary: King Leonidas of Sparta and a force of 300 men fight the Persians at Thermopylae in 480 B.C.

tagline: Definitely wanted
summary: In turn-of-the-century Mexico, two very different women become a bank-robbing duo in an effort to combat a ruthless enforcer terrorizing their town.

tagline: Becoming a woman. Becoming a legend.
summary: A biographical portrait of a pre-fame Jane Austen and her romance with a young Irishman.

tagline: The hardest trick is making them stay.
summary: A thirty-something preschool teacher looks to the personals for a change of pace and a relationship, with hilarious results.

tagline: Sit back. Relax. Enjoy the fright.
summary: An FBI agent takes on a plane full of deadly venomous snakes, deliberately released to kill a witness being flown from Honolulu to Los Angeles to testify against a mob boss.

tagline: How much will you risk?
summary: After suffering a career-ending knee injury, a former college football star aligns himself with one of the most renowned touts in the sports-gambling business.

tagline: The Avatar Returns
summary: In a war-torn world of elemental magic, a young boy reawakens to undertake a dangerous mystic quest to fulfill his destiny as the Avatar, and bring peace to the world.

primaryTitle: Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince
originalTitle: Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince
tagline: Once again I must ask too much of you, Harry.
summary: As Harry Potter begins his sixth year at Hogwarts, he discovers an old book marked as "the property of the Half-Blood Prince" and begins to learn more about Lord Voldemort's dark past.

tagline: Their war. Our world.
summary: An ancient struggle between two Cybertronian races, the heroic Autobots and the evil Decepticons, comes to Earth, with a clue to the ultimate power held by a teenager.

tagline: Én ulykke kommer sjældent alene [Scandinavian saying equivalent of: When it rains, it pours]
summary: A neo-nazi sentenced to community service at a church clashes with the blindly devotional priest.

tagline: Heroes are something we create, something we need.
summary: The life stories of the six men who raised the flag at the Battle of Iwo Jima, a turning point in World War II.

tagline: Every man fights his own war.
summary: A psychological study of a soldier's state of mind during the Gulf War. Told through the eyes of a U.S. Marine sniper who struggles to cope with boredom, a sense of isolation, and other issues back home.

tagline: Rise of the Zombies
summary: The living dead have taken over the world, and the last humans live in a walled city to protect themselves as they come to grips with the situation.

primaryTitle: The Three Burials of Melquiades Estrada
originalTitle: The Three Burials of Melquiades Estrada
tagline: Nobody is beyond redemption.
summary: Ranch foreman Pete Perkins looks to fulfill the promise to his recently deceased best friend by burying him in his hometown in Mexico.

tagline: He's in all of us.
summary: A disaffected soldier returns to his hometown to get even with the thugs who brutalized his mentally-challenged brother years ago.

tagline: Hell Breaks Loose
summary: Space Marines are sent to investigate strange events at a research facility on Mars but find themselves at the mercy of genetically enhanced killing machines.

tagline: Sometimes the best defense. . . is a wiseguy.
summary: In the late 1980s, a low level gangster named Jackie DiNorscio defends himself in court in what became the longest criminal trial in American judicial history.

tagline: Get ready to fall
summary: A sleazy writer has a chance to redeem himself when he goes to stay with his grandmother and befriends the neighbors.

tagline: There is a way to be good again.
summary: After spending years in California, Amir returns to his homeland in Afghanistan to help his old friend Hassan, whose son is in trouble.
A group of diamond thieves on the run kidnap the wife of a recently discharged marine who goes on a chase through the South Carolinian wilderness to retrieve her.

tagline: You thought your family was nuts
summary: Taken aback by his mother's wedding announcement, a young man returns home in an effort to stop her from marrying his old high school gym teacher, a man who made middle school hell for generations of students.

tagline: Harold Crick isn't ready to go. Full Stop.
summary: I.R.S. auditor Harold Crick suddenly finds himself the subject of narration only he can hear: narration that begins to affect his entire life, from his work, to his love-interest, to his death.

tagline: Small Mouse. Big Dreams.
summary: An unusually brave mouse helps to restore happiness to a forlorn kingdom after making friends with a gentleman rat.

tagline: They were given 2 weeks. It lasted 6 days.
summary: In 1971, twenty-four male students are selected to take on randomly assigned roles of prisoners and guards in a mock prison situated in the basement of the Stanford psychology building.

primaryTitle: The Texas Chainsaw Massacre: The Beginning
originalTitle: The Texas Chainsaw Massacre: The Beginning

summary: Before being sent to serve in Vietnam, two brothers and their girlfriends take one last road trip, but when they get into an accident, a terrifying experience will take them to a secluded house of horrors, with a chainsaw-wielding killer.

tagline: A Love Legend
summary: Veer-Zaara is a saga of love, separation, courage and sacrifice. A love story that is an inspiration and will remain a legend forever.

tagline: Heads You Live... Tails You Die.
summary: A recounting of Domino Harvey's life story. The daughter of actor Laurence Harvey turned away from her career as a Ford model to become a bounty hunter.

tagline: Their City. Their Rules. No Prisoners.
summary: An undercover cop, disillusioned by the death of his wife, is implicated in the murder of an officer and must struggle to clear himself.
A profile of Ian Curtis, the enigmatic singer of Joy Division whose personal, professional, and romantic troubles led him to commit suicide at the age of 23.

tagline: One goal. A second chance.
summary: Teenagers at a juvenile detention center, under the leadership of their counselor, gain self-esteem by playing football together.

tagline: This land will be civilized.
summary: A lawman apprehends a notorious outlaw and gives him nine days to kill his older brother, or else they'll execute his younger brother.

tagline: Fear Takes Flight
summary: A woman is kidnapped by a stranger on a routine flight. Threatened by the potential murder of her father, she is pulled into a plot to assist her captor in a political assassination.

tagline: The search for the Philosopher's stone continues!
summary: When a failed alchemical ritual leaves brothers Edward and Alphonse Elric with severely damaged bodies, they begin searching for the one thing that can save them; the fabled philosopher's stone.

primaryTitle: The Curious Case of Benjamin Button
originalTitle: The Curious Case of Benjamin Button
tagline: Life isn't measured in minutes, but in moments
summary: Tells the story of Benjamin Button, a man who starts aging backwards with consequences.

tagline: The Momma of all Comedies is Back.
summary: An FBI agent reprises his disguise as a corpulent old lady and takes a job as a nanny in a crime suspect's house.

tagline: The path to true love isn't always straight... (UK DVD Tagline)
summary: A newlywed bride becomes infatuated with another woman who questions her sexual orientation, promoting a stir among the bride's family and friends.

tagline: It's not a remake. It's not a sequel. And it's not based on a Japanese one.
summary: When a group of tourists in a New Orleans haunted swamp tour find themselves stranded in the wilderness, their evening of fun and spooks turns into a horrific nightmare.

tagline: Let Them Eat Cake
summary: The retelling of France's iconic but ill-fated queen, Marie Antoinette. From her betrothal and marriage to Louis XVI at 15 to her reign as queen at 19 and to the end of her reign as queen, and ultimately the fall of Versailles.
