summary: A behind-the-scenes look at the annual Penguin World Surfing Championship, and its newest participant, up-and-comer Cody Maverick.

tagline: Death, betrayal, and... hip hop!
summary: Fuu, a waitress who works in a teahouse, rescues two master swordsmen, Mugen and Jin, from their execution to help her find the "samurai who smells of sunflowers."
A transient young man breaks into empty homes to partake of the vacationing residents' lives for a few days.

tagline: When Charlie Bartlett listens everyone talks.
summary: A rich kid becomes the self-appointed psychiatrist to the student body of his new high school.

tagline: Someone's Going Down
summary: The story of an uptown rat that gets flushed down the toilet from his penthouse apartment, ending in the sewers of London, where he has to learn a whole new and different way of life.

tagline: Strangers shouldn't talk to little girls.
summary: Hayley's a smart, charming teenage girl. Jeff's a handsome, smooth fashion photographer. An Internet chat, a coffee shop meet-up, an impromptu fashion shoot back at Jeff's place. Jeff thinks it's his lucky night. He's in for a surprise.

tagline: Without an enemy there can be no war.
summary: In December 1914, an unofficial Christmas truce on the Western Front allows soldiers from opposing sides of the First World War to gain insight into each other's way of life.

tagline: No Missions, No Mutants, No Man of Steel, No Money, and No Bullshit Catchphrases
summary: A calamity at Dante and Randal's shops sends them looking for new horizons - but they ultimately settle at the fast food empire Mooby's.

primaryTitle: The Adventures of Sharkboy and Lavagirl 3-D
originalTitle: The Adventures of Sharkboy and Lavagirl 3-D
tagline: Everything that is... or was... began as a dream.
summary: A young boy is recruited by his imaginary friends Sharkboy and Lavagirl to help save their planet.

tagline: A huge comedy with tiny balls
summary: Down-and-out former professional ping-pong phenom, Randy Daytona, is sucked into a maelstrom when FBI Agent Ernie Rodriguez recruits him for a secret mission. Randy is determined to bounce back and win, and to smoke out his father's killer -- arch-fiend Feng.

tagline: Love is a high you can never come down from
summary: A poet falls in love with an art student who gravitates to his bohemian lifestyle -- and his love of heroin. Hooked as much on one another as they are on the drug, their relationship alternates between states of oblivion, self-destruction, and despair.

tagline: In order to get the girl, he's gotta get his shift together.
summary: A slacker competes with a repeat winner for the "Employee of the Month" title at work, in order to gain the affections of a new female employee.

tagline: Saving The World. And Loving It.
summary: Maxwell Smart, a highly intellectual but bumbling spy working for the CONTROL agency, is tasked with preventing a terrorist attack from rival spy agency KAOS.

tagline: In a town where nothing much goes on, a whole lot is about to go down
summary: A skilled London police officer is transferred to a small town with a dark secret.

tagline: Love will bring you back
summary: A lonely landscape architect falls for the spirit of the beautiful woman who used to live in his new apartment.

tagline: Your Numbers up, February 06
summary: A case of mistaken identity lands Slevin into the middle of a war being plotted by two of the city's most rival crime bosses. Under constant surveillance by Detective Brikowski and assassin Goodkat, he must get them before they get him.

tagline: Love. Commitment. Responsibility. There's nothing he won't run away from.
summary: Five years after jilting his pregnant fiancée on their wedding day, out-of-shape Dennis decides to run a marathon to win her back.

tagline: There is evidence to suggest that children are highly susceptible to paranormal phenomena. They see what adults cannot. They believe what adults deny. And they are trying to warn us.
summary: An ominous darkness invades a seemingly serene sunflower farm in North Dakota, and the Solomon family is torn apart by suspicion, mayhem and murder.

tagline: China, 208 A.D. The destiny of three kingdoms, and the fate of millions, would depend on the fight of a few.
summary: The first chapter of a two-part story centered on a battle fought in China's Three Kingdoms period (220-280 A.D.).

primaryTitle: The Suite Life of Zack & Cody
originalTitle: The Suite Life of Zack & Cody
tagline: This hotel is getting a wake up call.
summary: Comedy about identical twins living at the Tipton Hotel with their single mother who is a lounge singer at the hotel.

tagline: They're Hungry. You're Dinner.
summary: Patrons locked inside a bar are forced to fight monsters.

tagline: In 1943, one young woman stood up to the Nazis, her courage made her a legend, this is her story . . .
summary: A dramatization of the final days of Sophie Scholl, one of the most famous members of the German World War II anti-Nazi resistance movement, The White Rose.

tagline: The greatest Superhero movie of all time! (not counting all the others)
summary: Orphaned high school student Rick Riker is bitten by a radioactive dragonfly, develops super powers (except for the ability to fly), and becomes a hero.

tagline: How did a crime with this many witnesses go so far?
summary: Johnny and a couple pals kidnap Jake's 15-year-old brother, Zach, then assigns his buddy Frankie to be Zach's minder. They develop a brotherly friendship. Zach parties with his captors as things begin to spin out of control.

tagline: The music is everywhere. All you have to do is listen.
summary: An orphaned musical prodigy uses his gift to try to find his birth parents.

tagline: Takes One To Know One.
summary: When he finds out that his work superiors host a dinner celebrating the idiocy of their guests, a rising executive questions it when he's invited, just as he befriends a man who would be the perfect guest.

tagline: To leave the nest, some men just need a little push.
summary: A thirty-something is still living with his parents until they hire an interventionist to help him graduate out of the house. That's when the fun begins.

tagline: When the nation was in need, he inspired them to give us hope.
summary: A drama based on the true story of Melvin B. Tolson, a professor at Wiley College Texas. In 1935, he inspired students to form the school's first debate team, which went on to challenge Harvard in the national championship.

tagline: In nature, there are boundaries.
summary: A devastating and heart-rending take on grizzly bear activists Timothy Treadwell and Amie Huguenard, who were killed in October of 2003 while living among grizzly bears in Alaska.

tagline: On July 20th, the summer blockbuster is getting a whole new look.
summary: Pleasantly plump teenager Tracy Turnblad teaches 1962 Baltimore a thing or two about integration after landing a spot on a local TV dance show.

tagline: Do not trust anyone. Do not show emotion. Do not fall asleep.
summary: As a Washington, D.C. psychiatrist unearths the origin of an alien epidemic, she also discovers her son might be the only way it can be stopped.

tagline: Whoever has the money has the power
summary: Chris is a once promising high school athlete whose life is turned upside down following a tragic accident. As he tries to maintain a normal life, he takes a job as a janitor at a bank, where he ultimately finds himself caught up in a planned heist.

tagline: There's no smoke without liars.
summary: Satirical comedy follows the machinations of Big Tobacco's chief spokesman, Nick Naylor, who spins on behalf of cigarettes while trying to remain a role model for his 12-year old son.

tagline: Vengeance knows no mercy.
summary: A young fighter named Kham must go to Australia to retrieve his stolen elephant. With the help of a Thai-born Australian detective, Kham must take on all comers, including a gang led by an evil woman and her two deadly bodyguards.

tagline: In a town full of fiction, everyone has a version of the truth.
summary: A detective examines the mysterious death of George Reeves, the star of the television series Adventures of Superman (1952).

tagline: In the harshest place on Earth, love finds a way
summary: In the Antarctic, every March since the beginning of time, the quest begins to find the perfect mate and start a family.

tagline: There Is No Plan B...They Don't Need One.
summary: A group of Iraq War veterans look to clear their name with the U.S. Military, who suspect the four men of committing a crime for which they were framed.

tagline: This Summer It's Crunch Time.
summary: After Lucas Nickle floods an ant colony with his water gun, he's magically shrunken down to insect size and sentenced to hard labor in the ruins.

tagline: A Fish-Out-Of-Water Comedy.
summary: Two teenage girls discover a mermaid in their beach club's swimming pool.

tagline: Bobby Mercer is not the kind of man who asks twice
summary: When their adoptive mother is gunned down in a store robbery the 'four brothers' investigate the murder for themselves & look for the killers, but not all is what it seems.

tagline: From the Guys Who Brought You "White Chicks".
summary: A wannabe dad mistakes a vertically challenged criminal on the lam as his newly adopted son.

tagline: At the end of the day, what will you hang on to?
summary: A tale of an inner city drug dealer who turns away from crime to pursue his passion, rap music.

tagline: No Law
summary: Based on the 1980s TV action/drama, this update focuses on vice detectives Crockett and Tubbs as their respective personal and professional lives become dangerously intertwined.

tagline: Sometimes, the best way to get in the game is to throw out the rules.
summary: After a run-in with the law, Haley Graham (Missy Peregrym) is forced to return to the world from which she fled some years ago. Enrolled in an elite gymnastics program run by the legendary Burt Vickerman (Jeff Bridges), Haley's rebellious attitude gives way to something that just might be called team spirit.

tagline: Everything interesting begins in the mind.
summary: Novelist Catherine Tramell is once again in trouble with the law, and Scotland Yard appoints psychiatrist Dr. Michael Glass to evaluate her. Though, like Detective Nick Curran before him, Glass is entranced by Tramell and lured into a seductive game.

tagline: I am not a ROLE MODEL.
summary: Wild behavior forces a pair of energy drink reps to enroll in a Big Brother program.

tagline: Based on a true story.
summary: A young girl buys an antique box at a yard sale, unaware that inside the collectible lives a malicious ancient spirit. The girl's father teams with his ex-wife to find a way to end the curse upon their child.

tagline: An elite FBI team sent to find a killer in a hostile country
summary: A team of U.S. government agents are sent to investigate the bombing of an American facility in the Middle East.

tagline: Sometimes there's only one thing left to say.
summary: A young widow discovers that her late husband has left her 10 messages intended to help ease her pain and start a new life.

tagline: What Happens in Vegas... Stays In Vegas
summary: Survivors of the Raccoon City catastrophe travel across the Nevada desert, hoping to make it to Alaska. Alice joins the caravan and their fight against the evil Umbrella Corp.

tagline: Meryl Streep is The Brains Behind The Brains
summary: An urbane fox cannot resist returning to his farm raiding ways and then must help his community survive the farmers' retaliation.

tagline: Their PAST Has Come Back To HAUNT THEM
summary: A thick mist full of vengeful spirits haunts a prosperous island town off the coast of Oregon, as its inhabitants try to learn their town's dark secret in order to stop it.

tagline: Das Spiel geht weiter... (The game continues)
summary: A detective and his team must rescue 8 people trapped in a factory by the twisted serial killer known as Jigsaw.

tagline: Courage is stronger than steel.
summary: In the near future, robot boxing is a top sport. A struggling ex-boxer feels he's found a champion in a discarded robot.

tagline: People lie. Numbers don't.
summary: Working for the F.B.I., a mathematician uses equations to help solve various crimes.

tagline: In 2019, the most precious natural resource... is us.
summary: In the year 2019, a plague has transformed almost every human into vampires. Faced with a dwindling blood supply, the fractured dominant race plots their survival; meanwhile, a researcher works with a covert band of vamps on a way to save humankind.

tagline: In A Nation Terrorized By Its Own Government, One Man Dared to Tell The Truth
summary: Broadcast journalist Edward R. Murrow looks to bring down Senator Joseph McCarthy.

tagline: What Was Once Trapped, Will Now Be Unleashed
summary: Three interwoven stories about a terrible curse. A young woman encounters a malevolent supernatural force while searching for her missing sister in Tokyo; a mean high school prank goes horribly wrong; a woman with a deadly secret moves into a Chicago apartment building.
A tough-minded drama about two friends in South Central Los Angeles and the violence that comes between them.

tagline: He loves her. She loves him not.
summary: While visiting his hometown during Christmas, a man comes face-to-face with his old high school crush whom he was best friends with -- a woman whose rejection of him turned him into a ferocious womanizer.

tagline: We all make choices. What's yours?
summary: Michael'd have a great job, still have his 4 best friends, and be in love with a beautiful girl at 30. He loves Jenna but his life seems predictable until he meets a college girl. It seems that everybody's having relationship problems.

tagline: People should not be afraid of their governments. Governments should be afraid of their people.
summary: In a future British tyranny, a shadowy freedom fighter, known only by the alias of "V", plots to overthrow it with the help of a young woman.

tagline: Break through the Seireitei wall.
summary: High school student Ichigo Kurosaki, who has the ability to see ghosts, gains soul reaper powers from Rukia Kuchiki and sets out to save the world from "Hollows".

tagline: Afraid of the dark? You will be.
summary: A caving expedition goes horribly wrong, as the explorers become trapped and ultimately pursued by a strange breed of predators.

tagline: Search for truth. Find freedom.
summary: In a seemingly perfect community, without war, pain, suffering, differences or choice, a young boy is chosen to learn from an elderly man about the true pain and pleasure of the "real" world.

tagline: How do you solve a murder when the victim is you?
summary: A teenager is left invisible to the living after an attack.

tagline: Love is a force you can't control.
summary: Natalie, head of her curriculum activities in high school and riding on a tennis scholarship for college, gets Keith as her Chemistry lab partner. As Natalie can be uptight, Keith proves to be the opposite, even while hiding a secret.

tagline: If you can see the future, you can save it.
summary: A Las Vegas magician who can see into the future is pursued by FBI agents seeking to use his abilities to prevent a nuclear terrorist attack.

tagline: The Breakout Comedy Of The Summer
summary: The toys are mistakenly delivered to a day-care center instead of the attic right before Andy leaves for college, and it's up to Woody to convince the other toys that they weren't abandoned and to return home.
After she quits her lucrative job, Olivia finds herself unsure about her future and her relationships with her successful and wealthy friends.

tagline: Gadgets, Gizmos, Guinea Pigs. In 3-D.
summary: A specially trained squad of guinea pigs is dispatched to stop a diabolical billionaire from taking over the world.

tagline: Tradition Prepared Her. Change Will Define Her.
summary: After the death of Princess Diana, Queen Elizabeth II struggles with her reaction to a sequence of events nobody could have predicted.

tagline: Think you've seen it all? Think again. (Series 2)
summary: The further adventures in time and space of the alien adventurer known as the Doctor and their companions from planet Earth.

tagline: Her Legend Begins.
summary: A deactivated cyborg's revived, but can't remember anything of her past and goes on a quest to find out who she is.

tagline: This Summer, Evil Gets Raw.
summary: A group of delinquents are sent to clean the Blackwell Hotel. Little do they know reclusive psychopath Jacob Goodnight has holed away in the rotting hotel. When one of the teens is captured, those who remain - a group that includes the cop who put a bullet in Goodnight's head four years ago - band together to survive against the brutal killer.

tagline: Ba-Bawk-Bawk-Bawk
summary: Pop culture references fly thick and fast as stop-motion animation is featured in sketches lampooning everything from television movies to comic books.

tagline: Get off the bench and get into the game.
summary: A trio of guys try and make up for missed opportunities in childhood by forming a three-player baseball team to compete against standard children's Little League squads.

tagline: Kiss Your Ice Goodbye
summary: Manny, Sid, and Diego discover that the ice age is coming to an end, and join everybody for a journey to higher ground. On the trip, they discover that Manny, in fact, is not the last of the woolly mammoths.

tagline: Hopes, Dreams,l There Are No Ordinary Moments.
summary: A chance encounter with a stranger changes the life of a college gymnast.

tagline: We Fight Back
summary: In 2018, a mysterious new weapon in the war against the machines, half-human and half-machine, comes to John Connor on the eve of a resistance attack on Skynet. But whose side is he on, and can he be trusted?

tagline: A new series about *dealing* in the suburbs.
summary: When a suburban mother turns to dealing marijuana in order to maintain her privileged lifestyle after her husband dies, she finds out just how addicted her entire neighborhood already is.

tagline: Destroyed in love...
summary: A sweet blind girl Zooni meets a flirty Rehan. She ignores her friends' warnings. It's her time to discover life. Is she making the right love choice?

tagline: Feed the fear.
summary: A small town is taken over by an alien plague, turning residents into zombies and all forms of mutant monsters.

tagline: The most terrifying images are the ones that are real.
summary: A young photographer and his girlfriend discover mysterious shadows in their photographs after a tragic accident. They soon learn that you can not escape your past.

tagline: This Summer Jason Bourne Comes Home
summary: Jason Bourne dodges a ruthless C.I.A. official and his Agents from a new assassination program while searching for the origins of his life as a trained killer.

tagline: Summertime is Pandatime.
summary: The Dragon Warrior has to clash against the savage Tai Lung as China's fate hangs in the balance. However, the Dragon Warrior mantle is supposedly mistaken to be bestowed upon an obese panda who is a novice in martial arts.

tagline: It's the game of life and death....
summary: For a group of teens, the answer to the mysterious death of their old friend lies within the world of an online video game based on the true story of an ancient noblewoman known as the Blood Countess.
After her death, a mother returns to her home town in order to fix the situations she couldn't resolve during her life.

tagline: Evil breeds pain.
summary: The warrior Beowulf must fight and defeat the monster Grendel, who is terrorizing Denmark, and later, Grendel's Mother, who begins killing out of revenge.

As the American Civil War continues to rage, America's president struggles with continuing carnage on the battlefield as he fights with many inside his own cabinet on the decision to emancipate the slaves.

tagline: Can you solve the puzzle?
summary: The attempted assassination of the American President is told and re-told from several different perspectives.

tagline: 18 kids, one house, no way.
summary: A widowed Coast Guard Admiral and a widow handbag designer fall in love and marry, much to the dismay of her 10 and his 8 children.

primaryTitle: Borat: Cultural Learnings of America for Make Benefit Glorious Nation of Kazakhstan
originalTitle: Borat: Cultural Learnings of America for Make Benefit Glorious Nation of Kazakhstan
tagline: Come to Kazakhstan, It's Nice!
summary: Kazakh TV talking head Borat is dispatched to the United States to report on the greatest country in the world. With a documentary crew in tow, Borat becomes more interested in locating and marrying Pamela Anderson.

tagline: One night can change your whole life
summary: Two strangers stuck in Manhattan for the night grow into each other's most trusted confidants when an evening of unexpected adventure forces them to confront their fears and take control of their lives.

tagline: 10 will fight,9 will die.You get to watch.
summary: Jack Conrad is awaiting the death penalty in a corrupt Central American prison. He is "purchased" by a wealthy television producer and taken to a desolate island where he must fight to the death against nine other condemned killers from all corners of the world, with freedom going to the sole survivor.

tagline: All you have to do is dream.
summary: A trio of black female soul singers cross over to the pop charts in the early 1960s, facing their own personal struggles along the way.

tagline: Armed And Dangerously Dumb
summary: Little Red Riding Hood, the Wolf, the Woodsman, and Granny all tell the police the events that led up to their encounter.

tagline: Nothing is what it seems
summary: In turn-of-the-century Vienna, a magician uses his abilities to secure the love of a woman far above his social standing.

tagline: In 141 years, there's never been a traitor in the Secret Service.... Until Now.
summary: A Secret Service agent is framed as the mole in an assassination attempt on the President. He must clear his name and foil another assassination attempt while on the run from a Secret Service Protective Intelligence Division agent.

tagline: It takes a hero to change the world.
summary: In the prehistoric past, D'Leh is a mammoth hunter who bonds with the beautiful Evolet. When warriors on horseback capture Evolet and the tribesmen, D'Leh must embark on an odyssey to save his true love.

primaryTitle: The Assassination of Jesse James by the Coward Robert Ford
originalTitle: The Assassination of Jesse James by the Coward Robert Ford
tagline: Beyond the myth lies America's greatest betrayal.
summary: Robert Ford, who's idolized Jesse James since childhood, tries hard to join the reforming gang of the Missouri outlaw, but gradually becomes resentful of the bandit leader.

primaryTitle: The X Files: I Want to Believe
originalTitle: The X Files: I Want to Believe
tagline: Believe Again
summary: Mulder and Scully are called back to duty by the FBI when a former priest claims to be receiving psychic visions pertaining to a kidnapped agent.

tagline: When a series of murders terrorized California, one man took responsibility for them all.
summary: In the late 1960s/early 1970s, a San Francisco cartoonist becomes an amateur detective obsessed with tracking down the Zodiac Killer, an unidentified individual who terrorizes Northern California with a killing spree.

tagline: Some family secrets are best kept...buried.
summary: A pastor preoccupied with writing the perfect sermon fails to realize that his wife is having an affair, and his children are up to no good.

tagline: Himmel Eller Helvete - God Eller Ond - Nå Eller Aldri (Heaven or Hell - Good or Evil - Now or Never) [Norway]
summary: A former Christian missionary, who specializes in debunking religious phenomena, investigates a small town which seems to be suffering from the 10 biblical plagues.

tagline: The story of a man with small parts. (season 1)
summary: Andy Millman (Ricky Gervais) is an actor with ambition and a script. Reduced to working as an extra with a useless agent, Andy's attempts to boost his career invariably end in failure and embarrassment.

tagline: They lived without rules. They loved without fear. But as the world changed, so did they.
summary: The music of The Beatles and the Vietnam War form the backdrop for the romance between an upper-class American girl and a poor Liverpudlian artist.

tagline: Kick Some Ice
summary: In 2002, two rival Olympic ice skaters were stripped of their gold medals and permanently banned from men's single competition. Presently, however, they've found a loophole that will allow them to qualify as a pairs team.

tagline: One man's impossible dream... became his biggest triumph!
summary: Based on the story of Vince Papale, a 30-year-old bartender from South Philadelphia who overcame long odds to play for the NFL's Philadelphia Eagles in 1976.

tagline: Two Worlds, One War. The Ultimate Battle Begins.
summary: A Viking boy is left behind after his clan battles a Native American tribe. Raised within the tribe, he ultimately becomes their savior in a fight against the Norsemen.

tagline: An epic of epic epicness.
summary: In a magically realistic version of Toronto, a young man must defeat his new girlfriend's seven evil exes one by one in order to win her heart.

tagline: "Mastering others is strength. Mastering yourself makes you fearless." - Lao Tzu
summary: A biography of Chinese Martial Arts Master Huo Yuanjia, who is the founder and spiritual guru of the Jin Wu Sports Federation.

tagline: Forgiveness comes at a price
summary: A British medical doctor fights a cholera epidemic in a small Chinese village, while being trapped at home in a loveless marriage to an unfaithful wife.

tagline: What Happens When The Numbers Run Out?
summary: M.I.T. professor John Koestler links a mysterious list of numbers from a time capsule to past and future disasters and sets out to prevent the ultimate catastrophe.

tagline: Just say the word.
summary: A newly fostered young boy in search of his mother instead finds unexpected super powers and soon gains a powerful enemy.

tagline: Every second, somewhere in the universe, a sun dies. In 2007, it will be ours.
summary: A team of international astronauts are sent on a dangerous mission to reignite the dying Sun with a nuclear fission bomb in 2057.

tagline: He is saving the world whether we like it or not.
summary: Hancock is a superhero whose ill-considered behavior regularly causes damage in the millions. He changes when the person he saves helps him improve his public image.

tagline: Get ready for an adventure nine lifetimes in the making.
summary: An outlaw cat, his childhood egg-friend and a seductive thief kitty set out in search for the eggs of the fabled Golden Goose to clear his name, restore his lost honor and regain the trust of his mother and town.

tagline: Riders Wanted
summary: In his homeland of Alagaesia, a farm boy happens upon a dragon's egg -- a discovery that leads him on a predestined journey where he realizes he's the one person who can defend his home against an evil king.

tagline: Where's Olive?
summary: A family determined to get their young daughter into the finals of a beauty pageant take a cross-country trip in their VW bus.

primaryTitle: Pirates of the Caribbean: At World's End
originalTitle: Pirates of the Caribbean: At World's End
tagline: At the End of the World, the Adventure Begins
summary: Captain Barbossa, Will Turner and Elizabeth Swann must sail off the edge of the map, navigate treachery and betrayal, find Jack Sparrow, and make their final alliances for one last decisive battle.

tagline: One family. Eight wheels. No brakes.
summary: Bob Munro and his dysfunctional family rent an RV for a road trip to the Colorado Rockies, where they ultimately have to contend with a bizarre community of campers.

tagline: Pain is universal... But so is hope.
summary: Tragedy strikes a married couple on vacation in the Moroccan desert, touching off an interlocking story involving four different families.

tagline: The line between this world and the next is about to be crossed.
summary: A grief counselor working with a group of plane-crash survivors finds herself at the root of a mystery when her clients begin to disappear.
A sixteenth century love story about a marriage of alliance that gave birth to true love between a great Mughal emperor, Akbar, and a Rajput princess, Jodha.

tagline: The passionate life of Edith Piaf
summary: Biopic of the iconic French singer Édith Piaf. Raised by her grandmother in a brothel, she was discovered while singing on a street corner at the age of 19. Despite her success, Piaf's life was filled with tragedy.

tagline: 1 Witness... 118 Minutes...
summary: An aging alcoholic cop is assigned the task of escorting a witness from police custody to a courthouse 16 blocks away. There are, however, chaotic forces at work that prevent them from making it in one piece.

tagline: No one has found a diamond, Until Now
summary: A fisherman, a smuggler, and a syndicate of businessmen match wits over the possession of a priceless diamond.

tagline: 10,000 people are killed in America each year. Over 2,000 with firearms. Americans... they have no imagination...
summary: Three backpackers head to a Slovak city that promises to meet their hedonistic expectations, with no idea of the hell that awaits them.

tagline: Our Future Rests in His Hands.
summary: Frank Castle, known as the Punisher, ruthlessly demolishes organized crime, but it starts an even bigger war.

tagline: Kidnapper. Victim. Which are you?
summary: Five men wake up in a locked-down warehouse with no memory of who they are. They are forced to figure out who is good and who is bad to stay alive.

tagline: Some Sacrifices Must Be Made
summary: A sheriff investigating the disappearance of a young girl from a small island discovers there's a larger mystery to solve among the island's secretive, neo-pagan community.

tagline: The only demons in room 1408 are those within you.
summary: A man who specialises in debunking paranormal occurrences checks into the fabled room 1408 in the Dolphin Hotel. Soon after settling in, he confronts genuine terror.

primaryTitle: Cirque du Freak: The Vampire's Assistant
originalTitle: Cirque du Freak: The Vampire's Assistant
tagline: Meet Darren. He's sixteen going on immortal.
summary: Teenager Darren Shan meets a mysterious man at a freak show who turns out to be a vampire. After a series of events, Darren must leave his normal life and go on the road with the Cirque du Freak, becoming a creature of the night.

tagline: One Elephant One World One Story
summary: Horton the Elephant struggles to protect a microscopic community from his neighbors who refuse to believe it exists.

tagline: Coming For You
summary: After being wrongfully imprisoned for thirteen years and having her child taken away from her, a woman seeks revenge through increasingly brutal means.

tagline: Wonder. Power. Courage.
summary: When a pilot crashes and tells of conflict in the outside world, Diana, an Amazonian warrior in training, leaves home to fight a war, discovering her full powers and true destiny.

tagline: To catch a criminal, you have to think like one.
summary: The cases of the F.B.I. Behavioral Analysis Unit (B.A.U.), an elite group of profilers who analyze the nation's most dangerous serial killers and individual heinous crimes in an effort to anticipate their next moves before they strike again.

tagline: . . . pick a side.
summary: In a bid to keep their luxurious condo from their significant other, a couple's break-up proceeds to get uglier and nastier by the moment.

tagline: This Christmas, you better watch out!
summary: The Bakers, while on vacation, find themselves competing with a rival family of eight children.

tagline: Get ready for a killer ride.
summary: Ex-con Jensen Ames is forced by the warden of a notorious prison to compete in our post-industrial world's most popular sport: a car race in which inmates must brutalize and kill one another on the road to victory.

tagline: Hope begins where the secrets end.
summary: Two Boston area detectives investigate a little girl's kidnapping, which ultimately turns into a crisis both professionally and personally.

tagline: True love is a blessing and a curse. She's the blessing. He's cursed.
summary: In order to keep the woman of his dreams from falling for another guy, Charlie Logan has to break the curse that has made him wildly popular with single women: Sleep with Charlie once, and the next man you meet will be your true love.

tagline: Time is running out for a happy ending.
summary: Apartment building superintendent Cleveland Heep rescues what he thinks is a young woman from the pool he maintains. When he discovers that she is actually a character from a bedtime story who is trying to make the journey back to her home, he works with his tenants to protect his new friend from the creatures that are determined to keep her in our world.

primaryTitle: The Santa Clause 3: The Escape Clause
originalTitle: The Santa Clause 3: The Escape Clause
tagline: 'Twas the fight before Christmas
summary: Santa, a.k.a. Scott Calvin, is faced with double-duty: how to keep his new family happy and how to stop Jack Frost from taking over Christmas.
A Chicago librarian has a gene that causes him to involuntarily time travel, creating complications in his marriage.

tagline: Once you've checked in... The terror begins.
summary: A married couple becomes stranded at an isolated motel and finds hidden video cameras in their room. They soon realize that unless they escape, they'll be the next victims of a snuff film.

tagline: France doesn't stand a chance.
summary: Mr. Bean wins a trip to Cannes where he unwittingly separates a young boy from his father and must help the two reunite. On the way he discovers France, bicycling, and true love.

tagline: If you thought it was just a trick of the mind, prepare yourself for the truth.
summary: After a ferry is bombed in New Orleans, an A.T.F. agent joins a unique investigation using experimental surveillance technology to find the bomber, but soon finds himself becoming obsessed with one of the victims.

tagline: Raising Shell In 2007
summary: When the world is threatened by an ancient evil, the four adolescent turtles must reunite and overcome their faults in order to stand against it.

tagline: In a game divided by color, he made us see greatness.
summary: In 1947, Jackie Robinson becomes the first African-American to play in Major League Baseball in the modern era when he was signed by the Brooklyn Dodgers and faces considerable racism in the process.

tagline: From the creators of "Final Destination"
summary: On Christmas Eve, an escaped maniac returns to his childhood home, which is now a sorority house, and begins to murder the sorority sisters one by one.

tagline: Inspired by a true story
summary: The adventures of the Lafayette Escadrille, young Americans who volunteered for the French military before the U.S. entered World War I, and became the country's first fighter pilots.

tagline: They will be the last thing you ever see.
summary: A family falls victim to a group of mutated cannibals in a desert far away from civilization.

tagline: It looked like the perfect bank robbery. But you can't judge a crime by its cover.
summary: A police detective, a bank robber, and a high-power broker enter high-stakes negotiations after the criminal's brilliant heist spirals into a hostage situation.

tagline: Don't lose hope.
summary: A young man who survives a disaster at sea is hurtled into an epic journey of adventure and discovery. While cast away, he forms an unexpected connection with another survivor: a fearsome Bengal tiger.

tagline: There are some frequencies we were never meant to find
summary: When their computer hacker friend accidentally channels a mysterious wireless signal, a group of co-eds rally to stop a terrifying evil from taking over the world.

tagline: Inspired by a true story.
summary: A struggling salesman takes custody of his son as he's poised to begin a life-changing professional career.

tagline: Everybody has a secret... Duke wants Olivia who likes Sebastian who is really Viola whose brother is dating Monique so she hates Olivia who's with Duke to make Sebastian jealous who is really Viola who's crushing on Duke who thinks she's a guy...
summary: When her brother decides to ditch for a couple weeks, Viola heads over to his elite boarding school, disguised as him, and proceeds to fall for his school's star soccer player, and soon learns she's not the only one with romantic troubles.

tagline: This Christmas, Summer is really over
summary: A group of young backpackers' vacation turns sour when a bus accident leaves them marooned in a remote Brazilian rural area that holds an ominous secret.

tagline: Sometimes death is just the beginning. (season 5)
summary: Due to a political conspiracy, an innocent man is sent to death row and his only hope is his brother, who makes it his mission to deliberately get himself sent to the same prison in order to break the both of them out, from the inside.

tagline: Help Us
summary: After a strange and insecure plane crash, an unusual toxic virus enters a quaint farming town. A young couple are quarantined, but they fight for survival along with help from a couple of people.

primaryTitle: Garfield: A Tail of Two Kitties
originalTitle: Garfield: A Tale of Two Kitties
tagline: Too much of a good thing is even better.
summary: Jon and Garfield visit the United Kingdom, where a case of mistaken cat identity finds Garfield ruling over a castle. His reign is soon jeopardized by the nefarious Lord Dargis, who has designs on the estate.

primaryTitle: How to Lose Friends & Alienate People
originalTitle: How to Lose Friends & Alienate People
tagline: Brace yourselves, America.
summary: A British writer struggles to fit in at a high-profile magazine in New York City.

tagline: Charming. Magnetic. Murderous.
summary: Based on the events of the brutal Ugandan dictator Idi Amin's regime as seen by his personal physician during the 1970s.

tagline: You scream. You die.
summary: A young widower returns to his hometown to search for answers to his wife's murder, which may be linked to the ghost of a deceased ventriloquist.

Set in northern Australia before World War II, an English aristocrat who inherits a sprawling ranch reluctantly pacts with a stock-man in order to protect her new property from a takeover plot. As the pair drive 2,000 head of cattle over unforgiving landscape, they experience the bombing of Darwin, Australia, by Japanese forces firsthand.

tagline: Evil Hits Home
summary: During a babysitting gig, a high-school student is harassed by an increasingly threatening prank caller.

tagline: What do you see when you look at me?
summary: A man who believes he has put his mysterious past behind him cannot stand idly by when he meets a young girl under the control of ultra-violent Russian gangsters.

tagline: Tell me what the truth is
summary: Painter Francisco Goya faces a scandal involving his muse, who is labeled a heretic by a monk.

tagline: Never pick up strangers.
summary: A serial killer pins his crimes on two college students who gave him a ride.

tagline: Don't Get Mad, Get Even
summary: Three ex-girlfriends of a serial cheater set up their former lover to fall for the new girl in town so they can watch him get his heart broken.

tagline: Munnabhai meets Mahatma Gandhi
summary: Munna Bhai embarks on a journey with Mahatma Gandhi in order to fight against a corrupt property dealer.

tagline: A movie that proves you're never too old to come of age.
summary: A thirty-five-year-old video game tester has to move in with his grandma and her two old lady roommates.

tagline: When doing right goes very, very wrong.
summary: Things go wrong for a high ranking mobster when he doesn't proceed by his boss's orders.

tagline: Can you change your past without destroying your future?
summary: Nick Larson discovers a supernatural way to alter his life and travel back in time to key moments in his life by looking at photographs.

tagline: Universal Studios Invites You to Get Lost
summary: A space-time vortex sucks scientist Rick Marshall, his assistant Holly (Anna Friel) and a survivalist Will into a world populated by dinosaurs and painfully slow creatures called Sleestaks.

tagline: If you don't believe . . . You will.
summary: The young apprentice of a magical, eccentric toy store owner learns to believe in herself, and in her friends, upon learning some grave news about the future.

tagline: Open the door to another world and an exciting new vision in cinema
summary: In the Falangist Spain of 1944, the bookish young stepdaughter of a sadistic army officer escapes into an eerie but captivating fantasy world.

tagline: How Far Would You Go?
summary: A journalist goes undercover to ferret out businessman Harrison Hill as her childhood friend's killer. Posing as one of his temps, she enters into a game of online cat-and-mouse.

tagline: He's not lean. He's not mean. He's nacho average hero.
summary: Berated all his life by those around him, a monk follows his dream and dons a mask to moonlight as a Luchador (Mexican wrestler).

tagline: The perfect man. The perfect story. The perfect murder.
summary: An American journalism student in London scoops a big story, and begins an affair with an aristocrat as the incident unfurls.

tagline: Good dead are hard to find
summary: Space radiation turns the dead into Zombies. Zomcon fights zombies and finds ways to pacify and use them. On pre-teen Timmy's (Kesun Loder's) 1950s suburban street, they all have a zombie doing menial chores. Timmy's zombie becomes his pet and friend, and is named Fido (Sir Billy Connolly).

tagline: champagne is poured... secrets are spilled.
summary: A manager of an orphanage in India is sent to Copenhagen, Denmark, where he discovers a life-altering family secret.
Two women troubled with guy-problems swap homes in each other's countries, where they each meet a local guy and fall in love.

tagline: Steering the great ship of NEWS through the channels of TRUTH.
summary: Satirical newscaster Stephen Colbert provides humorous commentary on the big issues going on in the United States and the rest of the world, with his larger-than-life ego and overly-patriotic spirit along with him every step of the way.
Jedi Knights lead the Grand Army of the Republic against the droid army of the Separatists.

tagline: When patriots become heroes
summary: Steve Rogers, a rejected military soldier, transforms into Captain America after taking a dose of a "Super-Soldier serum". But being Captain America comes at a price as he attempts to take down a war monger and a terrorist organization.

tagline: Meet Andy Sachs. A million girls would kill to have her job. She's not one of them.
summary: A smart but sensible new graduate lands a job as an assistant to Miranda Priestly, the demanding editor-in-chief of a high fashion magazine.

tagline: Life is looking up.
summary: Four people meet on New Year's Eve, and form a surrogate family to help one another with the difficulties of their lives.

primaryTitle: Frank Miller's Sin City: A Dame to Kill For
originalTitle: Sin City: A Dame to Kill For
tagline: There is no justice without sin.
summary: Some of Sin City's most hard-boiled citizens cross paths with a few of its more reviled inhabitants.

tagline: Witness the Origin.
summary: The early years of James Logan, featuring his rivalry with his brother Victor Creed, his service in the special forces team Weapon X, and his experimentation into the metal-lined mutant Wolverine.

tagline: In my past life, I'd have stolen this magazine. Now I'm in it. Must be Karma...
summary: A ne'er do well wins $100,000 in the lottery and decides to right all the wrongs from his past with his newfound realization.

tagline: Chemistry keeps them together.
summary: Forensic anthropologist Dr. Temperance "Bones" Brennan and cocky F.B.I. Special Agent Seeley Booth build a team to investigate murders. Quite often, there isn't more to examine than rotten flesh or mere bones.

tagline: If he wasn't picked on he'd have no material.
summary: A young African-American teen attempts to survive with his dysfunctional family and his all-white school in the 1980s.

tagline: The dead are talking...and she is listening.
summary: A newlywed with the ability to communicate with the earthbound spirits of the recently deceased overcomes skepticism and doubt to help send their important messages to the living and allow the dead to pass on to the other side.

tagline: A love story in reverse.
summary: A father recounts to his children - through a series of flashbacks - the journey he and his four best friends took leading up to him meeting their mother.

tagline: For some people. Death is just a phrase (season 8)
summary: Two brothers follow their father's footsteps as hunters, fighting evil supernatural beings of many kinds, including monsters, demons and gods that roam the earth.

tagline: Time flies, but the good news is that you're the pilot.
summary: After a painful breakup, Ben develops insomnia. To kill time, he starts working the late night shift at the local supermarket, where his artistic imagination runs wild.

tagline: This man will bring order to the universe...or not.
summary: The story of an obsessively organized efficiency expert whose life unravels in unexpected ways when fate forces him to explore the serendipitous nature of love and forgiveness.

primaryTitle: In the Name of the King: A Dungeon Siege Tale
originalTitle: In the Name of the King: A Dungeon Siege Tale
tagline: Rise and fight
summary: A man named Farmer sets out to rescue his kidnapped wife and avenge the death of his son, two acts committed by the Krugs, a race of animal-warriors who are controlled by the evil Gallian.

tagline: A Little Blessing In Disguise.
summary: In a hospital on the outskirts of 1920s Los Angeles, an injured stuntman begins to tell a fellow patient, a little girl with a broken arm, a fantastic story of five mythical heroes. Thanks to his fractured state of mind and her vivid imagination, the line between fiction and reality blurs as the tale advances.

tagline: A Woman In Trouble
summary: As an actress begins to adopt the persona of her character in a film, her world becomes nightmarish and surreal.

primaryTitle: The Wind that Shakes the Barley
originalTitle: The Wind that Shakes the Barley
tagline: Winner of the PALME D'OR at the 2006 Cannes Film Festival.
summary: Against the backdrop of the Irish War of Independence, two brothers fight a guerrilla war against British forces.

tagline: The real world and the animated world collide.
summary: A young maiden in a land called Andalasia, who is prepared to be wed, is sent away to New York City by an evil Queen, where she falls in love with a lawyer.

tagline: The countdown begins...
summary: Vijay is recruited by a police officer to masquerade as his lookalike Don, the leader of an international gang of smugglers. Things go wrong when the officer is killed and Vijay is left to fend for himself.

tagline: To save his soul he must save hers.
summary: A God-fearing bluesman takes to a wild young woman who, as a victim of childhood sexual abuse, looks everywhere for love, never quite finding it.

tagline: A double feature that'll tear you in two!
summary: Quentin Tarantino and Robert Rodriguez's homage to exploitation double features in the '60s and '70s with two back-to-back cult films that include previews of coming attractions between them.

tagline: Leave the real world behind
summary: Life for the residents of a tower block begins to run out of control.

tagline: The Roman world is in the throes of death, but a new myth, destined to span the centuries, is waiting to be born.
summary: As the Roman empire crumbles, young Romulus Augustus flees the city and embarks on a perilous voyage to Britain to track down a legion of supporters.

tagline: It destroyed his world. He won't let it destroy ours.
summary: During the reign of the Vikings, Kainan, a man from a far-off world, crash lands on Earth, bringing with him an alien predator known as the Moorwen. Though both man and monster are seeking revenge for violence committed against them, Kainan leads the alliance to kill the Moorwen by fusing his advanced technology with the Viking's Iron Age weaponry.

tagline: In the Heart of the Jungle, Blood will Flow.
summary: In Thailand, John Rambo joins a group of mercenaries to venture into war-torn Burma, and rescue a group of Christian aid workers who were kidnapped by the ruthless local infantry unit.

tagline: Based on the extraordinary true story of one man's fight for freedom
summary: A U.S. fighter pilot's epic struggle of survival after being shot down on a mission over Laos during the Vietnam War.

tagline: Nice Guys Graduate Last.
summary: A young guy short on luck enrolls in a class to build confidence to help win over the girl of his dreams, which becomes complicated when it turns out his teacher has the same agenda.

tagline: See our family. And feel better about yours.

tagline: Every second chance begins with a first step.

tagline: Two's company. Dupree's a crowd.

tagline: When days turn to weeks, the horror returns.
summary: Six months after the rage virus was inflicted on the population of Great Britain, the US Army helps to secure a small area of London for the survivors to repopulate and start again. But not everything goes according to plan.
Astérix and Obélix compete at the Olympics in order to help their friend Lovesix marry Princess Irina. Brutus also tries to win the game with his own team and get rid of his father Julius Caesar.

primaryTitle: The Fast and the Furious: Tokyo Drift
originalTitle: The Fast and the Furious: Tokyo Drift
tagline: On the streets of Tokyo, speed needs no translation...
summary: A teenager becomes a major competitor in the world of drift racing after moving in with his father in Tokyo to avoid a jail sentence in America.

tagline: Their story. Their world. Their future.
summary: A young teacher inspires her class of at-risk students to learn tolerance, apply themselves and pursue education beyond high school.

tagline: Czech: Mrtvé deti si chtejí hrát (Dead children want to play)
summary: A woman brings her family back to her childhood home, which used to be an orphanage for handicapped children. Before long, her son starts to communicate with an invisible new friend.

tagline: This summer, how fast can you swim?
summary: After a sudden underwater tremor sets free scores of the prehistoric man-eating fish, an unlikely group of strangers must band together to stop themselves from becoming fish food for the area's new razor-toothed residents.

tagline: The Company Is Making Cutbacks
summary: During a team-building retreat in the mountains a group of sales representatives are hunted down one by one.

tagline: The film that terrified Europe has come to America

Benjamin Gates must follow a clue left in John Wilkes Booth's diary to prove his ancestor's innocence in the assassination of Abraham Lincoln.

A gun-for-hire known only as Agent 47 hired by a group known only as 'The Organization' is ensnared in a political conspiracy, which finds him pursued by both Interpol and the Russian military as he treks across Russia and Eastern Europe.

tagline: The truth is what he makes it.
summary: A law firm brings in its "fixer" to remedy the situation after a lawyer has a breakdown while representing a chemical company that he knows is guilty in a multibillion-dollar class action suit.

tagline: One woman's secret is another woman's power. One woman's fear is another woman's weapon. One woman's life is in another woman's hands....

tagline: Leurs pouvoirs font d'eux une espèce en danger (Their powers make them an endangered species)

tagline: No name, no past, nothing to lose.
summary: A man named Mr. Smith delivers a woman's baby during a shootout, and is then called upon to protect the newborn from the army of gunmen.

tagline: He wanted a break... Now she wants to break him.
summary: When a regular guy dumps a superhero for her neediness, she uses her powers to make his life a living hell.

tagline: From the eternal sea he rises. Creating armies on either shore. Turning man against his brother. Until man exists no more.

Coming together to solve a series of murders in New York City are a police detective and an assassin, who will be hunted by the police, the mob, and a ruthless corporation.

tagline: The only thing that could come between these sisters... is a kingdom.
summary: Two sisters contend for the affection of King Henry VIII.

tagline: A comedy about growing up... and the bumps along the way.
summary: Faced with an unplanned pregnancy, an offbeat young person makes an unusual decision regarding the unborn child.

tagline: Secrets don't let go.
summary: An inner-city junior high school teacher with a drug habit forms an unlikely friendship with one of his students after she discovers his secret.

tagline: Du är vad den äter. [You are what it eats] Swedish DVD release

tagline: In this world... redemption just comes once.
summary: Six days in the violent life of a young Johannesburg gang leader.

tagline: I Believe In Harvey Dent.
summary: When the menace known as the Joker wreaks havoc and chaos on the people of Gotham, Batman must accept one of the greatest psychological and physical tests of his ability to fight injustice.

tagline: Someone is trying to kill Alan. You'll wish it was you.

tagline: When Ambition Meets Faith
summary: A story of family, religion, hatred, oil and madness, focusing on a turn-of-the-century prospector in the early days of the business.

primaryTitle: Things We Lost in the Fire
originalTitle: Things We Lost in the Fire

summary: A recent widow invites her husband's troubled best friend to live with her and her two children. As he gradually turns his life around, he helps the family cope and confront their loss.

tagline: Every generation has a defining moment. This was ours.
summary: Two Port Authority police officers become trapped under the rubble of the World Trade Center.

tagline: First they send in their drone... then they find their queen.
summary: An unhinged war veteran holes up with a lonely woman in a spooky Oklahoma motel room. The line between reality and delusion is blurred as they discover a bug infestation.

tagline: To erase the line between man and machine is to obscure the line between men and gods
summary: A young programmer is selected to participate in a ground-breaking experiment in synthetic intelligence by evaluating the human qualities of a highly advanced humanoid A.I.
A struggling, suicidal young comedian meets a car thief who is willing to teach him a few things about his profession.

tagline: Coming soon to a town near you!

tagline: Ordinary guys. An extraordinary robbery.
summary: When a group of hard-working guys find out they've fallen victim to their wealthy employer's Ponzi scheme, they conspire to rob his high-rise residence.

tagline: (4) To Teach Us...
summary: A rag doll that awakens in a postapocalyptic future holds the key to humanity's salvation.

tagline: Takes out the fear residing deep inside our hearts.
summary: As the Mayan kingdom faces its decline, a young man is taken on a perilous journey to a world ruled by fear and oppression.

tagline: Based On The Outrageous True Story.

tagline: What makes us different makes us beautiful.
summary: A modern romantic tale about a young aristocratic heiress born under a curse that can only be broken when she finds true love with "one who will accept her as one of their own."

tagline: Smurfalicious (Smurfette poster)
summary: When the evil wizard Gargamel chases the tiny blue Smurfs out of their village, they tumble from their magical world into New York City.

tagline: The story of the man behind the legend.
summary: The life and death story of The Notorious B.I.G. (a.k.a. Christopher Wallace), who came straight out of Brooklyn to take the world of rap music by storm.

tagline: Someone has to fix the problems.
summary: An elite hitman teaches his trade to an apprentice who has a connection to one of his previous victims.

tagline: Tastes great. Less Fulfilling.
summary: Five friends with big egos and small brains are the proprietors of an Irish pub in Philadelphia.

primaryTitle: Prince of Persia: The Sands of Time
originalTitle: Prince of Persia: The Sands of Time
tagline: Defy the Future
summary: A young fugitive prince and princess must stop a villain who unknowingly threatens to destroy the world with a special dagger that enables the magic sand inside to reverse time.

tagline: If only life were as easy as pie.
summary: Jenna is a pregnant, unhappily married waitress in the deep south. She meets a newcomer to her town and falls into an unlikely relationship as a last attempt at happiness.

tagline: The Journey Continues...
summary: When Newcastle United soccer star Santiago Muñez (Kuno Becker) is offered a spot with Real Madrid, he accepts, but the move - accompanied by big money and fame - tests his ties and loyalties to family, friends, and business acquaintances.

tagline: So when do you know it's love?
summary: Two best friends being convinced that they are not in love search for each other's love.

originalTitle: Man cheng jin dai huang jin jia
tagline: Unspeakable secrets are hidden within the Forbidden City.
summary: During China's Tang dynasty the emperor has taken the princess of a neighboring province as wife. She has borne him two sons and raised his eldest. Now his control over his dominion is complete, including the royal family itself.

tagline: Who's telling the Lies?
summary: When a congressional aide is killed, a Washington, D.C. journalist starts investigating the case involving the Representative, his old college friend.
A beautiful woman helps an inept scam artist get his game together.

tagline: The war on terror begins with 40 ordinary people.
summary: A real-time account of the events on United Flight 93, one of the planes hijacked on September 11th, 2001 that crashed near Shanksville, Pennsylvania when passengers foiled the terrorist plot.

tagline: Lights. Camera. Abduction.
summary: A Hollywood fixer in the 1950s works to keep the studio's stars in line.

tagline: They're Dangerous, They're Even and they are after....
summary: When a Las Vegas performer-turned-snitch named Buddy Israel decides to turn state's evidence and testify against the mob, it seems that a whole lot of people would like to make sure he's no longer breathing.

tagline: Every hero has a code. (Season 1)
summary: Set at the intersection of the near future and the reimagined past, explore a world in which every human appetite can be indulged without consequence.

tagline: Only the power of hell can help them.
summary: Four young men who belong to a New England supernatural legacy are forced to battle a fifth power long thought to have died out. Meanwhile, jealousy and suspicion threaten to tear them apart.

tagline: Give him a room dad, he has no place to go...
summary: The family of a left-wing journalist is torn apart after the military coup of Turkey in 1980.

tagline: How many wrongs to make it right?
summary: Struggling to recover emotionally from a brutal assault that killed her fiancé and left her in a coma, a radio personality begins a quest for vengeance against the perpetrators that leaves a bloody trail across New York City.

tagline: Nice Guy. Huge Problem.
summary: A mild-mannered guy, who is married to a monstrous woman, meets the woman of his dreams, and schemes to find a way to be with her.

tagline: Reality is only a nightmare away
summary: A depressed woman learns that her husband was killed in a car accident the previous day, then awakens the next morning to find him alive and well at home; then awakens the day after that to find that he's dead.

tagline: 1 million tons of steel. 100,000 people at risk. 100 minutes to impact.
summary: With an unmanned, half-mile-long freight train barreling toward a city, a veteran engineer and a young conductor race against the clock to prevent a catastrophe.

tagline: Nobody's Perfect
summary: A film set in a strange afterlife way station that has been reserved for people who have committed suicide.

tagline: Extremely Sweet & Incredibly Heartwarming
summary: A nine-year-old amateur inventor, Francophile, and pacifist searches New York City for the lock that matches a mysterious key left behind by his father, who died in the World Trade Center on September 11, 2001.

tagline: At the Museum of Natural History, something unnatural is occurring.
summary: A newly recruited night security guard at the Museum of Natural History discovers that an ancient curse causes the animals and exhibits on display to come to life and wreak havoc.

tagline: One discovery can change your life. One mistake can destroy it.
summary: Violence and mayhem ensue after a hunter stumbles upon a drug deal gone wrong and more than two million dollars in cash near the Rio Grande.

tagline: Inspired by the true story of five students who changed the game forever.

tagline: One Father's Fight To Find The Truth.

tagline: Expected in cinemas soon.
summary: For fun-loving party animal Ben Stone, the last thing he ever expected was for his one-night stand to show up on his doorstep eight weeks later to tell him she's pregnant with his child.

tagline: It ain't over 'til it's over.
summary: Thirty years after the ring of the first bell, Rocky Balboa comes out of retirement and dons his gloves for his final fight against the reigning heavyweight champ Mason 'The Line' Dixon.

tagline: How Fast Can You Swim?
summary: An American journalist on assignment in the Australian outback encounters a man-eating crocodile while trapped on a rapidly flooding mud island.

tagline: Vengeance never rests.
summary: At the end of the Civil War, a colonel hunts down a man with whom he has a grudge.

tagline: If his heart stops pumping adrenalin... It will be the day Chev Chelios dies
summary: Professional assassin Chev Chelios learns his rival has injected him with a poison that will kill him if his heart rate drops.

tagline: Still together. Still lost!
summary: The Madagascar animals fly back to New York City, but crash-land on an African nature reserve, where they meet others of their own kind, and Alex especially discovers his royal heritage as prince of a lion pride.

tagline: What will it sound like when you die?
summary: Several people start receiving voice-mails from their future selves - messages which include the date, time, and some of the details of their deaths.

tagline: This January Raise Some Hell.
summary: Fourteenth century knights transport a suspected witch to a monastery, where monks deduce her powers could be the source of the Black Plague.

tagline: Run with the crowd, stand alone, you decide.
summary: A young boy becomes friends with a gang of skinheads. Friends soon become like family, and relationships will be pushed to the very limit.

tagline: Something's happening to Dan. It's confusing. It's awkward. It's family.
summary: A widower finds out the woman he fell in love with is his brother's girlfriend.

tagline: Before Logan... There was... I Am Legend.
summary: Years after a plague kills most of humanity and transforms the rest into monsters, the sole survivor in New York City struggles valiantly to find a cure.

tagline: You Don't Give Them Orders. You Just Turn Them Loose.
summary: A CIA special forces team are betrayed and left for dead by their superiors, galvanizing them to mount an offensive on the CIA.

tagline: A Trip Back in Time... from Present to Crime
summary: A man accidentally gets into a time machine and travels back in time nearly an hour. Finding himself will be the first of a series of disasters of unforeseeable consequences.

tagline: Good for one week off marriage.
summary: Rick and Fred, two husbands who are having difficulty in their marriages, are given a Hall Pass by their wives: for one week, they can do whatever they want.

tagline: Something's Cooking This Summer
summary: The life of a top chef changes when she becomes the guardian of her young niece.

tagline: A number is just a number. Or is it?
summary: Walter Sparrow becomes obsessed with a novel that he believes was written about him, as more and more similarities between himself and his literary alter ego seem to arise.

tagline: The Journey Begins
summary: After their cave is destroyed, a caveman family must trek through an unfamiliar fantastical world with the help of an inventive boy.

primaryTitle: Harold & Kumar Escape from Guantanamo Bay
originalTitle: Harold & Kumar Escape from Guantanamo Bay
tagline: What would NPH do?
summary: After being mistaken for terrorists and thrown into Guantánamo Bay, stoners Harold and Kumar escape and return to the U.S., where they proceed to flee across the country with federal agents in hot pursuit.

tagline: On the French Riviera, Love, Passion and Romance come at a Price
summary: Through a set of wacky circumstances, a young gold digger mistakenly woos a mild-mannered bartender, thinking he's a wealthy suitor.

tagline: He's trying to get out of her knickers
summary: Sworn enemies find themselves in each other's bodies, and use this to ruin each other's lives.

tagline: One of the greatest love stories never told
summary: The story of Beatrix Potter, the author of the beloved and best-selling children's book, "The Tale of Peter Rabbit", and her struggle for love, happiness, and success.

tagline: Are You Watching Closely?
summary: After a tragic accident, two stage magicians engage in a battle to create the ultimate illusion while sacrificing everything they have to outwit each other.

tagline: Truth. Honor. Loyalty. Family. What are you willing to sacrifice?
summary: A family's moral codes are tested when Ray Tierney investigates a case that reveals an incendiary police corruption scandal involving his own brother-in-law. For Ray, the truth is revelatory, a Pandora's Box that threatens to upend not only the Tierney legacy but the entire NYPD.

tagline: The most terrifying images are the ones that are real.
summary: A newly married couple discovers disturbing, ghostly images in photographs they develop after a tragic accident. Fearing the manifestations may be connected, they investigate and learn that some mysteries are better left unsolved.

tagline: Because you were home.
summary: A young couple staying in an isolated vacation home are terrorized by three unknown assailants.

tagline: The End Is Nigh.
summary: A futuristic action thriller where a team of people work to prevent a disaster threatening the future of the human race.

tagline: From the director of RAIN MAN and GOOD MORNING, VIETNAM
summary: A comedian who hosts a news satire program decides to run for president, and a computerized voting machine malfunction gets him elected.

tagline: We Are Coming (Series 3)

tagline: Turn the darkness into light
summary: A young boy in a remote medieval outpost under siege from barbarian raids is beckoned to adventure when a celebrated master illuminator arrives with an ancient book, brimming with secret wisdom and powers.

tagline: Sometimes the things we can't change...end up changing us.

A businessman bets his life on a horse race; a gangster sees the future; a pop star falls prey to a crime boss; a doctor must save the love of his life.

summary: A boy stands on a station platform as a train is about to leave. Should he go with his mother or stay with his father? Infinite possibilities arise from this decision. As long as he doesn't choose, anything is possible.

summary: A crew of African American pilots in the Tuskegee training program, having faced segregation while kept mostly on the ground during World War II, are called into duty under the guidance of Col. A.J. Bullard.

tagline: America is being born again
summary: A documentary on kids who attend a summer camp hoping to become the next Billy Graham.

tagline: From the comic geniuses who brought you the phenomenon "Super Troopers".
summary: Two brothers travel to Germany for Oktoberfest, only to stumble upon a secret, centuries-old competition described as a "Fight Club" with beer games.

primaryTitle: Fantastic 4: Rise of the Silver Surfer
tagline: Who will rise?
summary: The Fantastic Four learn that they aren't the only super-powered beings in the universe when they square off against the powerful Silver Surfer and the planet-eating Galactus.

tagline: Santa's brother is coming to town.
summary: Fred Claus, Santa's bitter older brother, is forced to move to the North Pole to help Santa and the elves prepare for Christmas in exchange for cash.

tagline: The fairytale that won't behave
summary: In a countryside town bordering on a magical land, a young man makes a promise to his beloved that he'll retrieve a fallen star by venturing into the magical realm.

tagline: In Hollywood, everybody can hear you scream.
summary: Two weeks in the life of a fading Hollywood producer who's having a rough time trying to get his new picture made.

tagline: The quieter the street, the darker the secrets....
summary: A teen living under house arrest becomes convinced his neighbor is a serial killer.

tagline: Ride hard... or stay home!
summary: A group of suburban biker wannabes looking for adventure hit the open road, but get more than they bargained for when they encounter a New Mexico gang called the Del Fuegos.
The comedic misadventures of Roy, Moss and their grifting supervisor Jen, a rag-tag team of IT support workers at a large corporation headed by a hotheaded yuppie.

tagline: They wrote the book on how not to be criminals.
summary: A frustrated, unemployed professor joins forces with a scammer and a friend of his in a blackmailing scheme.

tagline: I shot my wife... prove it.
summary: An attorney intending on climbing the career ladder toward success finds an unlikely opponent in a manipulative criminal he is trying to prosecute.
At Oxford University, a professor and a grad student work together to try to stop a potential series of murders seemingly linked by mathematical symbols.

tagline: Coming soon to our galaxy
summary: Star Wars fanatics take a cross-country trip to George Lucas' Skywalker Ranch so their dying friend can see a screening of Star Wars: Episode I - The Phantom Menace (1999) before its release.

tagline: Anywhere. Anything. Instantly.
summary: A teenager with teleportation abilities suddenly finds himself in the middle of an ancient war between those like him and their sworn annihilators.

tagline: A comedy about life at the top, as seen from the bottom.

tagline: Every game has its loopholes...
summary: Jigsaw abducts a doctor in order to keep himself alive while he watches his new apprentice put an unlucky citizen named Jeff through a brutal test.

tagline: No one knows how far they can go... until they are pushed.
summary: A perfect family's dynamic is ruined by a kidnapper's brutally efficient plot.
A human detective and a fairy rekindle a dangerous affair in a Victorian fantasy world, where the city's uneasy peace collapses when a string of murders reveals an unimaginable monster.

primaryTitle: All the Boys Love Mandy Lane
originalTitle: All the Boys Love Mandy Lane
tagline: She's To Die For
summary: A group of high-schoolers invite Mandy Lane, an innocent, desirable girl, to a weekend party on a secluded ranch. While the festivities rage on, the number of revelers begins to drop mysteriously.

tagline: She's just your normal, overprotective, overbearing, over-the-top mother.
summary: A meddling mother tries to set her daughter up with the right man so her kid won't follow in her footsteps.

tagline: He'll have to kick some butt to save his own.
summary: A weak con man panics when he learns he's going to prison for fraud. He hires a mysterious martial arts guru who helps transform him into a martial arts expert who can fight off inmates who want to hurt or love him.

tagline: Welcome to the 23rd century. The new dark ages.
summary: 28th century soldier Mitch Hunter leads a fight against an army of underworld Mutants.

tagline: In a city of millions, finding one can change your whole life
summary: A man who lost his family in the September 11 attack on New York City runs into his old college roommate. Rekindling the friendship is the one thing that appears able to help the man recover from his grief.

tagline: Sometimes silence is the deadliest sound.
summary: In the 17th century, two Portuguese Jesuit priests travel to Japan in an attempt to locate their mentor, who is rumored to have committed apostasy, and to propagate Catholicism.

tagline: It's a thin line between love and friendship.
summary: Friendships are tested and secrets come to the surface when terminally single Rachel falls for Dex, her best friend Darcy's fiancé.

tagline: Where your problems disappear.
summary: As a 1950s suburban community self-destructs, a home invasion has sinister consequences for one seemingly normal family.

tagline: All the law. None of the order.
summary: A novice sleuth is hired by the Police after he cons them into thinking he has psychic powers which help solve crimes. With the assistance of his reluctant best friend, the duo take on a series of complicated cases.

tagline: What if the only explanation for what you saw was unbelievable?

tagline: He had the perfect game plan. There's just one little problem...

tagline: On Stage She's a Superstar.But at Home She Leads A Totally Normal Life!
summary: Adventures of a teenage pop star who keeps her identity secret from even her closest friends by using a disguise on-stage.

tagline: Chip Happens

summary: Chris Pontius, Johnny Knoxville, Steve-O, Bam Margera, and the whole crew return to the screen to raise the stakes higher than ever before.

primaryTitle: This Film Is Not Yet Rated
originalTitle: This Film Is Not Yet Rated
tagline: censorship, uncensored.
summary: Kirby Dick's exposé about the American movie ratings board.

tagline: Choose your destiny.
summary: A frustrated office worker learns that he is the son of a professional assassin and that he shares his father's superhuman killing abilities.

tagline: Every story ever written is just waiting to become real.

tagline: There was a time when humans and dragons were one. [USA release]
summary: In a mythical land, a man and a young boy investigate a series of unusual occurrences.

tagline: Enjoy the ride. (Season 2)
summary: Liz Lemon (Tina Fey), head writer of the sketch comedy show "TGS with Tracy Jordan", must deal with an arrogant new boss and a crazy new star, all while trying to run a successful television show without losing her mind.

summary: Danny Ocean rounds up the boys for a third heist after casino owner Willy Bank double-crosses one of the original eleven, Reuben Tishkoff.

tagline: We're all on thin ice.

tagline: Life is the ultimate work of art.

tagline: From the director of "Flags of our Fathers" comes the story of the battle for Iwo Jima told through the eyes of the Japanese soldiers.
summary: The story of the battle of Iwo Jima between the United States and Imperial Japan during World War II, as told from the perspective of the Japanese who fought it.

originalTitle: Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 2

originalTitle: Legend of the Guardians: The Owls of Ga'Hoole
