Four incompetent British terrorists set out to train for and commit an act of terror.

tagline: How do you know when you're in luck?
summary: After being cut from the U.S.A. softball team and feeling a bit past her prime, Lisa finds herself evaluating her life and in the middle of a love triangle, as a corporate guy in crisis competes with her current, baseball-playing beau.

tagline: They were careless people, Tom and Daisy-they smashed up things and creatures and then retreated back into their money or their vast carelessness...
summary: A writer and wall street trader, Nick, finds himself drawn to the past and lifestyle of his millionaire neighbor, Jay Gatsby.

primaryTitle: The Girl Who Kicked the Hornet's Nest
tagline: Part 3 of The Millennium Trilogy
summary: Lisbeth is recovering in a hospital and awaiting trial for three murders when she is released. Mikael must prove her innocence, but Lisbeth must be willing to share the details of her sordid experiences with the court.

tagline: Judgment is coming
summary: In a violent, futuristic city where the police have the authority to act as judge, jury and executioner, a cop teams with a trainee to take down a gang that deals the reality-altering drug, SLO-MO.

tagline: Comedy. Out of bounds.
summary: Three incoming freshmen attending Midwestern college football powerhouse Blue Mountain State must quickly adapt to college life and juggle football, girls, classes and nonstop hazing.

tagline: Rise
summary: Eight years after the Joker's reign of anarchy, Batman, with the help of the enigmatic Catwoman, is forced from his exile to save Gotham City from the brutal guerrilla terrorist Bane.

tagline: Prepare for a giant adventure
summary: The ancient war between humans and a race of giants is reignited when Jack, a young farmhand fighting for a kingdom and the love of a princess, opens a gateway between the two worlds.

tagline: Intriguing, darkly erotic!
summary: Suspecting her husband of infidelity, gynecologist Dr. Catherine Stewart hires an escort named Chloe in order to test his faithfulness. Soon, the relationships between all three intensify.

tagline: Live for Love
summary: Life changes in an instant for young Mia Hall after a car accident puts her in a coma. During an out-of-body experience, she must decide whether to wake up and live a life far different than she had imagined. The choice is hers if she can go on.

tagline: The true story of one man against the biggest drug cartel in history
summary: A U.S. Customs official uncovers a money laundering scheme involving Colombian drug lord Pablo Escobar.
Two brothers search for a Philosopher's Stone after an attempt to revive their deceased mother goes awry and leaves them in damaged physical forms.

tagline: Every Moment Counts
summary: A malfunction in a sleeping pod on a spacecraft traveling to a distant colony planet wakes one passenger 90 years early.

tagline: Keep your enemies close.
summary: The true story of Whitey Bulger, the brother of a state senator and the most infamous violent criminal in the history of South Boston, who became an FBI informant to take down a Mafia family invading his turf.

tagline: Let the games begin.
summary: A white-collar criminal agrees to help the FBI catch other white-collar criminals using his expertise as an art and securities thief, counterfeiter, and conman.
The mysterious disappearance of a kindergarten teacher during a picnic in the north of Iran is followed by a series of misadventures for her fellow travelers.

tagline: Child. Captive. Killer.
summary: A drama based on the experiences of Agu, a child soldier fighting in the civil war of an unnamed African country.

tagline: Her legend begins.
summary: Lara Croft (Alicia Vikander), the fiercely independent daughter of a missing adventurer, must push herself beyond her limits when she discovers the island where her father, Lord Richard Croft (Dominic West) disappeared.

tagline: Worst. Babysitter. Ever.
summary: A college student on suspension is coaxed into babysitting the kids next door, though he is fully unprepared for the wild night ahead of him.

tagline: Hai tempo fino all'alba per riprenderti la tua famiglia. (You have until dawn to take back your family. - Italian DVD)
summary: After his family is kidnapped during their sailing trip in Spain, a young Wall Street trader is confronted by the people responsible: intelligence agents looking to recover a mysterious briefcase.

tagline: Only Sanity Can Keep You Alive
summary: An institutionalized young woman becomes terrorized by a ghost.

tagline: Everything Is Connected
summary: An exploration of how the actions of individual lives impact one another in the past, present and future, as one soul is shaped from a killer into a hero, and an act of kindness ripples across centuries to inspire a revolution.

primaryTitle: This Is Where I Leave You
originalTitle: This Is Where I Leave You
tagline: Welcome Home. Get Uncomfortable.
summary: After their father passes away, four grown siblings are forced to return to their childhood home and live under the same roof for a week, along with their over-sharing mother and an assortment of spouses, exes and might-have-beens.

tagline: Nature Teaches Beasts to Know Their Friends
summary: A banished hero of Rome allies with a sworn enemy to take his revenge on the city.

tagline: Slay with pride. Kill with prejudice.
summary: Five sisters in 19th century England must cope with the pressures to marry while protecting themselves from a growing population of zombies.

tagline: Two worlds. One future.
summary: Adam and Eden fell in love as teens despite the fact that they live on twinned worlds with gravities that pull in opposite directions. Ten years after a forced separation, Adam sets out on a dangerous quest to reconnect with his love.

tagline: Your mind is the scene of the crime
summary: A thief who steals corporate secrets through the use of dream-sharing technology is given the inverse task of planting an idea into the mind of a C.E.O.

tagline: Back Then They Were Too Young To Know Better. Now They Have No Excuse.
summary: After their high school basketball coach passes away, five good friends and former teammates reunite for a Fourth of July holiday weekend.

The Naval Criminal Investigation Service's Office of Special Projects takes on the undercover work and the hard to crack cases in LA. Key agents are G. Callen and Sam Hanna, streets kids risen through the ranks.
A rich man's daughter is held captive in an abandoned apartment by two former convicts who abducted her and hold her ransom in exchange for her father's money.

tagline: The cat is the most feared animal there is!
summary: Three teenagers live isolated, without leaving their house, because their over-protective parents say they can only leave when their dogtooth falls out.

tagline: You can't escape the past
summary: After a journalist discovers his identity, a former Weather Underground activist goes on the run.

tagline: Your Path Has Been Adjusted
summary: The affair between a politician and a contemporary dancer is affected by mysterious forces keeping the lovers apart.

tagline: Rock out with your Glock out
summary: Jimmy's rare baseball card is robbed. Since it's his only hope to pay for his daughter's upcoming wedding, he recruits his cop partner Paul to track down the robber, a memorabilia-obsessed gangster.

tagline: When the cops are busy... Our only hope is...
summary: Two mismatched New York City detectives seize an opportunity to step up like the city's top cops, whom they idolize, only things don't quite go as planned.

tagline: In squad we trust
summary: A secret government agency recruits some of the most dangerous incarcerated super-villains to form a defensive task force. Their first mission: save the world from the apocalypse.

tagline: Is it real Is it recall
summary: A factory worker, Douglas Quaid, begins to suspect that he is a spy after visiting Rekall - a company that provides its clients with implanted fake memories of a life they would like to have led - goes wrong and he finds himself on the run.
Centering on Ip Man's migration to Hong Kong in 1949 as he attempts to propagate his discipline of Wing Chun martial arts.

tagline: See life in a big way
summary: A social satire in which a man realizes he would have a better life if he were to shrink himself to five inches tall, allowing him to live in wealth and splendor.

tagline: They don't make 'em like they used to.
summary: A pair of aging stickup men try to get the old gang back together for one last hurrah before one of the guys takes his last assignment - to kill his comrade.

tagline: Based on a true story.
summary: Set in Southern California, a father moves his young family to the countryside to renovate and re-open a struggling zoo.

primaryTitle: In the Heart of the Sea
originalTitle: In the Heart of the Sea
tagline: Experience the true encounter that inspired the myth Moby Dick.
summary: A recounting of a New England whaling ship's sinking by a giant whale in 1820, an experience that later inspired the great novel Moby-Dick.

tagline: The Games Will Change Everyone
summary: Katniss Everdeen voluntarily takes her younger sister's place in the Hunger Games: a televised competition in which two teenagers from each of the twelve Districts of Panem are chosen at random to fight to the death.

tagline: WHAT A LOVELY DAY (all caps One Sheet)
summary: In a post-apocalyptic wasteland, a woman rebels against a tyrannical ruler in search for her homeland with the aid of a group of female prisoners, a psychotic worshiper, and a drifter named Max.

tagline: A hidden truth. A desperate search.
summary: When Keller Dover's daughter and her friend go missing, he takes matters into his own hands as the police pursue multiple leads and the pressure mounts.
The life of a businessman begins to change after he inherits six penguins, and as he transforms his apartment into a winter wonderland, his professional side starts to unravel.

tagline: You'll float too.
summary: In the summer of 1989, a group of bullied kids band together to destroy a shape-shifting monster, which disguises itself as a clown and preys on the children of Derry, their small Maine town.

tagline: First they took his daughter. Now they're coming for him.
summary: In Istanbul, retired CIA operative Bryan Mills and his wife are taken hostage by the father of a kidnapper Mills killed while rescuing his daughter.

tagline: An action-packed, fun-filled family adventure!
summary: Sean Anderson partners with his mom's husband on a mission to find his grandfather, who is thought to be missing on a mythical island.

tagline: The group that defined a generation becomes a movie of our time.
summary: The rap group NWA emerges from the mean streets of Compton in Los Angeles, California, in the mid-1980s and revolutionizes Hip Hop culture with their music and tales about life in the hood.

tagline: Earth goes dark
summary: The Autobots learn of a Cybertronian spacecraft hidden on the moon, and race against the Decepticons to reach it and to learn its secrets.

tagline: Everyone's got a secret
summary: An unflinching Ozark Mountain girl hacks through dangerous social terrain as she hunts down her drug-dealing father while trying to keep her family intact.

tagline: Be ready to believe in Santa again.
summary: In the depths of the Korvatunturi mountains, 486 meters deep, lies the closest ever guarded secret of Christmas. The time has come to dig it up. This Christmas everyone will believe in Santa Claus.

tagline: Take back your life.
summary: A man awakens from a coma, only to discover that someone has taken on his identity and that no one, (not even his wife), believes him. With the help of a young woman, he sets out to prove who he is.

tagline: Every step counts.
summary: Mumble's son, Erik, is struggling to realize his talents in the Emperor Penguin world. Meanwhile, Mumble and his family and friends discover a new threat their home -- one that will take everyone working together to save them.

tagline: Sometimes life gives you the finger and sometimes it gives you...
summary: A young boy has lost his mother and is losing touch with his father and the world around him. Then he meets Hesher who manages to make his life even more chaotic.

tagline: Punishment comes one way or another
summary: A stubborn teenager enlists the help of a tough U.S. Marshal to track down her father's murderer.

tagline: Live in the moments.
summary: A romantic drama centered on two new lovers: Tyler, whose parents have split in the wake of his brother's suicide, and Ally, who lives each day to the fullest since witnessing her mother's murder.

tagline: For anyone who has to break up with their best friend.
summary: A divorcing couple tries to maintain their friendship while they both pursue other people.

tagline: You remember your first kiss forever... and ever
summary: The lives, loves, dangers and disasters in the town, Mystic Falls, Virginia. Creatures of unspeakable horror lurk beneath this town as a teenage girl is suddenly torn between two vampire brothers.

tagline: In our darkest hour, when our leaders have fallen, a hero will rise.
summary: After the crew of the Enterprise find an unstoppable force of terror from within their own organization, Captain Kirk leads a manhunt to a war-zone world to capture a one-man weapon of mass destruction.

tagline: Propose to this cop's sister? Rookie mistake.
summary: Security guard Ben must prove himself to his girlfriend's brother, top police officer James. He rides along James on a 24-hour patrol of Atlanta.

tagline: They are back... in time.
summary: Agent J travels in time to M.I.B.'s early days in 1969 to stop an alien from assassinating his friend Agent K and changing history.
An American finds refuge during the 1937 Japanese invasion of Nanking in a church with a group of women. Posing as a priest, he attempts to lead the women to safety.

tagline: Friendship has its benefits
summary: A guy and girl try to keep their relationship strictly physical, but it's not long before they learn that they want something more.

tagline: Survival Is His Revenge
summary: Left for dead on a sun-scorched planet, Riddick finds himself up against an alien race of predators. Activating an emergency beacon alerts two ships: one carrying a new breed of mercenary, the other captained by a man from Riddick's past.

tagline: "No one here has to know."
summary: Two years after the bachelor party in Las Vegas, Phil, Stu, Alan, and Doug jet to Thailand for Stu's wedding. Stu's plan for a subdued pre-wedding brunch, however, goes seriously awry.

tagline: Candy, Chicks, and Rock 'n' Roll
summary: E.B., the Easter Bunny's teenage son, heads to Hollywood, determined to become a drummer in a rock 'n' roll band. In LA, he's taken in by Fred after the out-of-work slacker hits E.B. with his car.

tagline: For seven strangers, this is just the beginning of an exotic adventure.
summary: British retirees travel to India to take up residence in what they believe is a newly restored hotel. Less luxurious than advertised, the Marigold Hotel nevertheless slowly begins to charm in unexpected ways.

tagline: Don't Fit In? Take A Number.
summary: Eloise, having been relieved of maid of honor duties after being unceremoniously dumped by the best man via text, decides to attend the wedding anyway, only to find herself seated with five fellow unwanted guests at the dreaded Table 19.

tagline: On September 11, 2001 the world watched in terror. On September 12, 2001 they volunteered to fight.
summary: 12 Strong tells the story of the first Special Forces team deployed to Afghanistan after 9/11; under the leadership of a new captain, the team must work with an Afghan warlord to take down the Taliban.

tagline: In a war between kings even a pawn can change the game
summary: An entry-level employee at a powerful corporation finds himself occupying a corner office, but at a dangerous price: he must spy on his boss's old mentor to secure for him a multi-billion dollar advantage.

tagline: What doesn't kill you... is going to marry your brother.
summary: When a young woman realizes her brother is about to marry the girl who bullied her in high school, she sets out to expose the fiancée's true colors.

originalTitle: Nanny McPhee and the Big Bang
tagline: You'll Believe That Pigs Can Fly!
summary: Nanny McPhee arrives to help a harried young mother who is trying to run the family farm while her husband is away at war, though she uses her magic to teach the woman's children and their two spoiled cousins five new lessons.
The lives and tragedies of the Braverman family tree.

tagline: Based on the true story of Danny Greene the man the mob couldn't kill
summary: The true story of Danny Greene, a tough Irish thug working for mobsters in Cleveland during the 1970's.

tagline: In the battle between good and evil, an immortal holds the key.
summary: Frankenstein's creature finds himself caught in an all-out, centuries old war between two immortal clans.
After withdrawing to the Chateau Marmont, a passionless Hollywood actor reexamines his life when his eleven-year-old daughter surprises him with a visit.

tagline: Out there, there's nowhere to hide
summary: A group of mountaineers in the Scottish Highlands discover a kidnapped girl and are pursued by her captors.

tagline: Some People Tell Lies. Others Live Them.
summary: A convicted arsonist looks to manipulate a parole officer into a plan to secure his parole by placing his beautiful wife in the lawman's path.

tagline: The Hunt Is On
summary: A group of elite warriors parachute into an unfamiliar jungle and are hunted by members of a merciless alien race.

tagline: No Fear. No Limits. No Equal.
summary: A documentary on Brazilian Formula One racing driver Ayrton Senna, who won the F1 world championship three times before his death at age 34.
A semi-autobiographical story about Hubert as a young homosexual at odds with his mother.

tagline: X marks the legend.
summary: The story of Linda Lovelace, who is used and abused by the porn industry at the behest of her coercive husband before taking control of her life.

tagline: Revenge is sweeter than candy.
summary: Hansel & Gretel are bounty hunters who track and kill witches all over the world. As the fabled Blood Moon approaches, the siblings encounter a new form of evil that might hold a secret to their past.
Bo is a supernatural being who challenges her clan's way of life.

tagline: The fight of his life will be for his own.
summary: Wolverine comes to Japan to meet an old friend whose life he saved years ago, and gets embroiled in a conspiracy involving yakuza and mutants.

tagline: Operation Santa Claus is coming to town!
summary: Santa's clumsy son Arthur sets out on a mission with Grandsanta to give out a present they misplaced to a young girl in less than two hours.

tagline: No mercy, no escape, no time.
summary: An undercover Detroit cop navigates a dangerous neighborhood that's surrounded by a containment wall with the help of an ex-con in order to bring down a crime lord and his plot to devastate the entire city.

originalTitle: The Pirates! In an Adventure with Scientists!
tagline: Bring me my brown pants
summary: Pirate Captain sets out on a mission to defeat his rivals Black Bellamy and Cutlass Liz for the Pirate of the year Award. The quest takes Captain and his crew from the shores of Blood Island to the foggy streets of Victorian London.

tagline: Justice has a new face
summary: A wisecracking mercenary gets experimented on and becomes immortal but ugly, and sets out to track down the man who ruined his looks.
A look at four seasons in the lives of a happily married couple and their relationships with their family and friends.

tagline: This year, the holidays come faster.
summary: An ex-con gets on a series of apparently unrelated killings. He gets tracked by a veteran cop with secrets of his own and an egocentric hit man.

tagline: Look Up
summary: A drama centered on a group of people searching for human connections in today's wired world.

tagline: A new romantic comedy
summary: The truth of how Mortimer Granville devised the invention of the first vibrator in the name of medical science.

tagline: One man's tyranny threatens the fate of a nation. Now a few will face impossible odds.
summary: A group of assassins come together for a suicide mission to kill an evil lord.

tagline: Love at first fight (character poster)
summary: When Blu, a domesticated macaw from small-town Minnesota, meets the fiercely independent Jewel, he takes off on an adventure to Rio de Janeiro with the bird of his dreams.

tagline: Someone is Watching Over YOU.
summary: You wake day after day to the comfort and security of your home. But how safe is it really?

tagline: You can't run from evil when it lives next door.
summary: When a nice new neighbor moves in next door, Charley discovers that he is an ancient vampire who preys on the community. Can he save his neighborhood from the creature with the help of the famous "vampire killer", Peter Vincent?

tagline: Life is for living
summary: Charlie's brother, Sam, dies in a car crash that Charlie survives. Charlie is given the gift of seeing his dead brother and others who he has lost such as his friend who died in the military, but when the girl he falls in love with's life is at risk, he must choose between his girlfriend and his brother.

tagline: A Modern Love Story
summary: A chef and a scientist fall in love as an epidemic begins to rob people of their sensory perceptions.

tagline: Mastering the B.S. degree at community college.
summary: A suspended lawyer is forced to enroll in a community college with an eccentric staff and student body.

tagline: The Battle for Earth Begins at Sea
summary: A fleet of ships is forced to do battle with an armada of unknown origins in order to discover and thwart their destructive goals.

tagline: Life starts now.
summary: An irreverent young woman who uses her humor to prevent matters from getting serious has a life-changing visit with her doctor.

tagline: A comedy that doesn't let principles stand in the way of progress.
summary: 15-year-old Oliver Tate has two objectives: To lose his virginity before his next birthday, and to extinguish the flame between his mother and an ex-lover who has resurfaced in her life.

tagline: Never for money Always for love
summary: Cheyenne, a retired rock star living off his royalties in Dublin, returns to New York City to find the man responsible for a humiliation suffered by his recently deceased father during W.W.II.

tagline: George Clooney is
summary: An assassin hides out in Italy for one last assignment.

tagline: Brand new season. Brand new episodes. Brand new network. (Season 4)
summary: Follows the escapades and relationships of a group of neighbors living in Gulfhaven, Florida.

tagline: Everyone in the world will get a flash of their own future.
summary: A special task force in the FBI investigates after every person on Earth simultaneously blacks out and awakens with a short vision of their future.
Haunted by painful memories and increasing paranoia, a damaged woman struggles to re-assimilate with her family after fleeing an abusive cult.
A mysterious young woman seduces lonely men in the evening hours in Scotland. However, events lead her to begin a process of self-discovery.

tagline: Life is too big to walk it alone.
summary: A father heads overseas to recover the body of his estranged son who died while traveling the "El camino de Santiago," and decides to take the pilgrimage himself.

tagline: Make the impossible possible.
summary: A fisheries expert is approached by a consultant to help realize a sheik's vision of bringing the sport of fly-fishing to the desert and embarks on an upstream journey of faith and fish to prove the impossible possible.

tagline: Divided by war. United by love.
summary: A British woman recalls coming of age during World War I - a story of young love, the futility of war, and how to make sense of the darkest times.

tagline: The Gold Standard
summary: Three different but related families face trials and tribulations in their own uniquely comedic ways.

tagline: The End Begins (Season 3)
summary: The life of Spartacus, the gladiator who lead a rebellion against the Romans. From his time as an ally of the Romans, to his betrayal and becoming a gladiator, to the rebellion he leads and its ultimate outcome.

tagline: Don't let the name fool you.
summary: Alicia Florrick (Julianna Margulies) has been a good wife to her husband, a former state's attorney. After a very humiliating sex and corruption scandal, he is behind bars. She must now provide for her family and returns to work as a litigator in a law firm.

tagline: Just like your family...kind of. Not really. Well, maybe.
summary: The daily mishaps of a married woman and her semi-dysfunctional family and their attempts to survive life in general in the town of Orson, Indiana.

tagline: Naughty, nice. You better believe.
summary: When the evil spirit Pitch launches an assault on Earth, the Immortal Guardians team up to protect the innocence of children all around the world.

tagline: Discover what Mankind was never meant to see
summary: Following clues to the origin of mankind, a team finds a structure on a distant moon, but they soon realize they are not alone.

tagline: May the Best Man Live
summary: When his mentor is taken captive by a disgraced Arab sheik, a killer-for-hire is forced into action. His mission: kill three members of Britain's elite Special Air Service responsible for the death of his sons.

tagline: No one gets off. Until he does.
summary: A corrupt, junkie cop with bipolar disorder attempts to manipulate his way through a promotion in order to win back his wife and daughter while also fighting his own inner demons.

tagline: Before They Were Incorporated, They Had To Be Educated
summary: A look at the relationship between Mike Wazowski (Billy Crystal) and James P. "Sully" Sullivan (John Goodman) during their days at Monsters University, when they weren't necessarily the best of friends.

tagline: Change begins with a whisper.
summary: An aspiring author during the civil rights movement of the 1960s decides to write a book detailing the African American maids' point of view on the white families for which they work, and the hardships they go through on a daily basis.

tagline: Don't Let Go
summary: Two astronauts work together to survive after an accident leaves them stranded in space.

tagline: Meet Doug, The Nicest Guy You'll Ever Fight.
summary: Labeled an outcast by his brainy family, a bouncer overcomes long odds to lead a team of under performing misfits to semi-pro hockey glory, beating the crap out of everything that stands in his way.

tagline: Where Were You When Everything Changed?
summary: When their country is invaded and their families are taken, eight unlikely teenagers band together to fight.

tagline: Evil Loves Innocence.
summary: Paranormal investigators Ed and Lorraine Warren work to help a family terrorized by a dark presence in their farmhouse.

tagline: They messed with the wrong mother.
summary: A mother stops at nothing to recover her kidnapped son.

tagline: Lose who you are to save what you love.
summary: A married couple's life is turned upside down when the wife is accused of a murder.

tagline: Once upon a time, there were two little girls who lived in a house.
summary: Soon after moving into their seemingly idyllic new home, a family learns of a brutal crime committed against former residents of the dwelling.

tagline: We're not just fighting for our lives. We're fighting for our existence.
summary: Survivors of an alien attack on earth gather together to fight for their lives and fight back.

tagline: Paul Conroy Isn't Ready To Die.
summary: Paul is a U.S. truck driver working in Iraq. After an attack by a group of Iraqis he wakes to find he is buried alive inside a coffin. With only a lighter and a cell phone it's a race against time to escape this claustrophobic death trap.

primaryTitle: The Odd Life of Timothy Green
originalTitle: The Odd Life of Timothy Green
tagline: He's a force of nature.
summary: A childless couple bury a box in their backyard, containing all of their wishes for an infant. Soon, a child is born, though Timothy Green is not all that he appears.

tagline: In Martial Arts there is no right or wrong, only the last man standing.
summary: The story of martial-arts master Ip Man, the man who trained Bruce Lee.

primaryTitle: Big Mommas: Like Father, Like Son
originalTitle: Big Mommas: Like Father, Like Son
tagline: Momma's got back-up.
summary: Malcolm Turner and his stepson Trent go undercover at an all-girls school to flush out a killer.
Aliens and their Guardians are hiding on Earth from intergalactic bounty hunters. They can only be killed in numerical order, and Number Four is next on the list. This is his story.

tagline: The Most Dangerous Thing Is To Be Alive.
summary: In a world of vampires, an expert vampire hunter and his young protégé travel toward sanctuary.

tagline: He doesn't need words.
summary: A mute bartender goes up against his city's gangsters in an effort to find out what happened to his missing partner.

tagline: When it comes to break-ups... he's the business
summary: Alex and his sister run a business designed to break up relationships. They are hired by a rich man to break up the wedding of his daughter. The only problem is that they only have one week to do so.

tagline: The perfect love story... with a high body count...
summary: Affable hillbillies Tucker and Dale are on vacation at their dilapidated mountain cabin when they are mistaken for murderers by a group of preppy college students.

tagline: Just one more thing...
summary: Los Angeles homicide detective Lieutenant Columbo uses his humble ways and ingenuous demeanor to winkle out even the most well-concealed of crimes.

tagline: 100% medically accurate.
summary: A mad scientist kidnaps and mutilates a trio of tourists in order to reassemble them into a human centipede, created by stitching their mouths to each others' rectums.

tagline: Beaches ain't ready
summary: Devoted lifeguard Mitch Buchannon butts heads with a brash new recruit, as they uncover a criminal plot that threatens the future of the bay.

tagline: The Ultimate Tool
summary: Former special operative MacGruber is called back into action to take down his arch-enemy, Dieter Von Cunth, who's in possession of a nuclear warhead and bent on destroying Washington, D.C.

tagline: 13 July. A NASA space probe crashed in Mexico. Its mission was to find life elsewhere. Its search is over.
summary: Six years after Earth has suffered an alien invasion, a cynical journalist agrees to escort a shaken American tourist through an infected zone in Mexico to the safety of the U.S. border.

tagline: Old flame. New fling. Big problem.
summary: Forty-something and single again, Bridget decides to focus on her job and surround herself with friends. In a twist, she finds herself pregnant, but with one hitch - she can only be fifty percent sure of the identity of her baby's father.
A student tries to fix a problem he accidentally caused in OZ, a digital world, while pretending to be the fiancé of his friend at her grandmother's 90th birthday.

tagline: What if you were on the Devil's side without knowing it?
summary: DCI John Luther is a near-genius murder detective whose brilliant mind can't always save him from the dangerous violence of his passions.

tagline: The Game is On
summary: A modern update finds the famous sleuth and his doctor partner solving crime in 21st century London.

tagline: In eye-popping 3D
summary: As a deadly battle rages over Jigsaw's brutal legacy, a group of Jigsaw survivors gathers to seek the support of self-help guru and fellow survivor Bobby Dagen, a man whose own dark secrets unleash a new wave of terror.

tagline: Discover The Man You Never Knew
summary: A compilation of interviews, rehearsals, and backstage footage of Michael Jackson as he prepared for his series of sold-out shows in London.

tagline: He's not from around here.
summary: Arthur Curry, the human-born heir to the underwater kingdom of Atlantis, goes on a quest to prevent a war between the worlds of ocean and land.

tagline: Today Is The First Day... Of The Rest Of His Weekend.
summary: Tim Lippe has no idea what he's in for when he's sent to Cedar Rapids, Iowa to represent his company at an annual insurance convention, where he soon finds himself under the "guidance" of three convention veterans.
Competition between the maid of honor and a bridesmaid, over who is the bride's best friend, threatens to upend the life of an out-of-work pastry chef.

tagline: Inner City vs. Outer Space
summary: A teen gang in South London defend their block from an alien invasion.

tagline: The purest form of war is one on one.
summary: Two veterans of the Bosnian War, one American, one Serbian, find their unlikely friendship tested when one of them reveals their true intentions.

tagline: How far can he go before he goes too far?
summary: Riding across Manhattan in a stretch limo in order to get a haircut, a 28-year-old billionaire asset manager's day devolves into an odyssey with a cast of characters that start to tear his world apart.

An ensemble comedy that follows a group of old friends in a fantasy football league who care deeply about one another -- so deeply that they use every opportunity to make each other's lives miserable.

tagline: Go get yourself loved.

primaryTitle: Sherlock Holmes: A Game of Shadows
originalTitle: Sherlock Holmes: A Game of Shadows

primaryTitle: The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo
originalTitle: The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo

tagline: Summer of Answers. (Season 6A)

tagline: The class of '99 returns for their high school reunion.

primaryTitle: A Good Day to Die Hard

tagline: Be first. Be smarter. Or cheat.

summary: Beca, a freshman at Barden University, is cajoled into joining The Bellas, her school's all-girls singing group. Injecting some much needed energy into their repertoire, The Bellas take on their male rivals in a campus competition.

tagline: Meet Matilda
summary: When an island populated by happy, flightless birds is visited by mysterious green piggies, it's up to three unlikely outcasts - Red, Chuck and Bomb - to figure out what the pigs are up to.

primaryTitle: Cloudy With a Chance of Meatballs 2
originalTitle: Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs 2
tagline: Peel out.
summary: Flint Lockwood now works at The Live Corp Company for his idol Chester V. But he's forced to leave his post when he learns that his most infamous machine is still operational, and is churning out menacing food-animal hybrids.

tagline: Everyone deserves a 24th chance.
summary: Ex baseball player Charlie is an anger management therapist with small group sessions at home. He has an OCD teen daughter, an ex-wife and a sex buddy/therapist.

tagline: Based on a true story.
summary: A comedic look at the relationship between a wealthy man with quadriplegia and an unemployed man with a criminal record who's hired to help him.

tagline: Friendship doesn't have an off switch.
summary: In the near future, an ex-jewel thief receives a gift from his son: a robot butler programmed to look after him. But soon the two companions try their luck as a heist team.

summary: Six tourists hire an extreme tour guide who takes them to the abandoned city Pripyat, the former home to the workers of the Chernobyl nuclear reactor. During their exploration, they soon discover they are not alone.

tagline: Tell yourself it's just a game.
summary: Desperate to help her ailing brother, a young woman unknowingly agrees to compete in a deadly game of "Would You Rather," hosted by a sadistic aristocrat.

tagline: Trained to kill. Left for dead. Back for more.
summary: The U.S. government recruits Machete to battle his way through Mexico in order to take down an arms dealer who looks to launch a weapon into space.

tagline: Family vs. frat
summary: After they are forced to live next to a fraternity house, a couple with a newborn baby do whatever they can to take them down.

tagline: An American dream.
summary: Loosely based on the true story of two young men, David Packouz and Efraim Diveroli, who won a three hundred million dollar contract from the Pentagon to arm America's allies in Afghanistan.

tagline: The hunter becomes the hunted
summary: An Alaska State Trooper partners with a young woman who escaped the clutches of serial killer Robert Hansen to bring the murderer to justice. Based on actual events.

tagline: Hope Runs Deep
summary: Based on the real-life event, when a gold and copper mine collapses, it traps 33 miners underground for 69 days.

tagline: Ikineba. (We must live.)
summary: A look at the life of Jiro Horikoshi, the man who designed Japanese fighter planes during World War II.

tagline: All heroes start somewhere.
summary: A group of intergalactic criminals must pull together to stop a fanatical warrior with plans to purge the universe.
India's top spy Tiger and his love Zoya battle the dark world of intelligence and espionage that forbids its soldiers from loving the enemy.

tagline: No rules. No mercy. Pure fighting.
summary: A young martial artist's unparalleled Tai Chi skills land him in a highly lucrative underworld fight club.

tagline: Get ready to get naughty!
summary: The Smurfs team up with their human friends to rescue Smurfette, who has been abducted by Gargamel, since she knows a secret spell that can turn the evil sorcerer's newest creation, creatures called "The Naughties", into real Smurfs.

tagline: Never Give Up
summary: After a collision with a shipping container at sea, a resourceful sailor finds himself, despite all efforts to the contrary, staring his mortality in the face.

tagline: Old habits die hard. (Season 3)
summary: An ex-con assumes the identity of a murdered sheriff in the small town of Banshee, Pennsylvania; where he has some unfinished business.

tagline: They've come home, but not alone.
summary: After a young couple take in their two nieces, they suspect that a supernatural spirit named Mama has latched onto their family.

tagline: Killers have never been this close-knit.
summary: Chris wants to show girlfriend Tina his world, but events soon conspire against the couple and their dream caravan holiday takes a very wrong turn.

tagline: Is this the face of a sucker?
summary: Mild mannered businessman Sandy Patterson travels from Denver to Florida to confront the deceptively harmless looking woman who has been living it up after stealing Sandy's identity.

tagline: The Hijacking Was Just the Beginning
summary: An air marshal springs into action during a transatlantic flight after receiving a series of text messages demanding $150 million into an off-shore account, or someone will die every 20 minutes.

tagline: Sometimes love can conquer fate. Sometimes not.
summary: Elise and Didier fall in love at first sight, in spite of their differences. He talks, she listens. He's a romantic atheist, she's a religious realist. When their daughter becomes seriously ill, their love is put on trial.

tagline: The extraordinary true story of Solomon Northup
summary: In the antebellum United States, Solomon Northup, a free black man from upstate New York, is abducted and sold into slavery.

tagline: The impossible rescue.

tagline: A comedy about acting your age and other adult decisions
summary: In the throes of a quarter-life crisis, Megan panics when her boyfriend proposes, then, taking an opportunity to escape for a week, hides out in the home of her new friend, 16-year-old Annika, who lives with her world-weary single dad.

summary: In ancient China, a group of European mercenaries encounters a secret army that maintains and defends the Great Wall of China against a horde of monstrous creatures.

tagline: The Only way out is All in.

Ciro disregards tradition in his attempt to become the next boss of his crime syndicate. The internal power struggle puts him and his entire family's life at risk.

tagline: Fear. Sacrifice. Contact.
summary: An international crew of astronauts undertakes a privately funded mission to search for life on Jupiter's fourth largest moon.

Put in charge of his young son, Alain leaves Belgium for Antibes to live with his sister and her husband as a family. Alain's bond with Stephanie, a killer whale trainer, grows deeper after Stephanie suffers a horrible accident.

tagline: This is your insanity on drugs.
summary: A young woman's world unravels when a drug prescribed by her psychiatrist has unexpected side effects.

tagline: Say hello to Samantha... Miss Jones, if you're nasty! (Season 2)
summary: Carrie Bradshaw is in her junior year of high school in the early 1980s. She asks her first questions about love, sex, friendship and family while navigating the worlds of high school and Manhattan.
The vacation of a famous rock star and her boyfriend in Italy is disrupted by the unexpected visit of an old friend and his daughter.

tagline: The commander is in England. The drone pilot is in America. The terrorist is in Kenya. And the authority to strike is up in the air.

tagline: Revenge is never a straight line.

tagline: Justice has no limit

tagline: You don't play the game. It plays you.

tagline: The Only Way to Tell His Story is to live His Fantasy.

tagline: 15 years after the blackout...they will light the way.
summary: Fifteen years after a permanent global blackout, a group of revolutionaries seeks to drive out an occupying force posing as the United States Government.

tagline: The moment you wake up, the nightmare begins
summary: A man wakes up in the wilderness, in a pit full of dead bodies, with no memory and must determine if the murderer is one of the strangers who rescued him, or if he himself is the killer.

tagline: Joe Caroll Was Just The Beggining.
summary: A brilliant and charismatic, yet psychotic serial killer communicates with other active serial killers and activates a cult of believers following his every command.

tagline: Don't judge a cop by his cover.
summary: A cop with a connection to the criminal underworld scours a nightclub in search of his kidnapped son.
From dawn to dusk, a few hours in the shadowy life of a mystic man named Monsieur Oscar.

tagline: Whatever Life Throws at You
summary: A daughter tries to remedy her dysfunctional relationship with her ailing father, a decorated baseball scout, by helping him in a recruiting trip which could be his last.

tagline: Unlock the secret, win the war
summary: During World War II, the English mathematical genius Alan Turing tries to crack the German Enigma code with help from fellow mathematicians.
A man and woman are drawn together, entangled in the life cycle of an ageless organism. Identity becomes an illusion as they struggle to assemble the loose fragments of wrecked lives.

tagline: >> The future is bright./ (season 3)
summary: An anthology series exploring a twisted, high-tech multiverse where humanity's greatest innovations and darkest instincts collide.

tagline: The hunt is on.
summary: A young teenager camping in the woods helps rescue the President of the United States when Air Force One is shot down near his campsite.

tagline: What's your price?
summary: A salesman for a natural gas company experiences life-changing events after arriving in a small town, where his corporation wants to tap into the available resources.

tagline: They make a killer couple.
summary: A girl falls for the "perfect" guy, who happens to have a very fatal flaw: he's a hitman on the run from the crime cartels who employ him.

tagline: Every second counts
summary: A father struggles to keep his infant daughter alive in the wake of Hurricane Katrina.

tagline: Genius Cannot Be Contained. (Series 1)
summary: Follows Leonardo Da Vinci during his early days in Florence, as a young artist, inventor and dreamer, trying to change the future.

tagline: Welcome to the Spanish Inquisition.
summary: Callum Lynch explores the memories of his ancestor Aguilar de Nerha and gains the skills of a Master Assassin, before taking on the secret Templar society.

summary: 20 years since their first adventure, Lloyd and Harry go on a road trip to find Harry's newly discovered daughter, who was given up for adoption.

tagline: Meet the little voices inside your head.

tagline: Champions can come from anywhere

tagline: When it comes to getting action, leave your inhibitions behind.

tagline: Actual friends. Actual dares. Actually funny.

tagline: Revenge is coming.
summary: In New York City, a crime lord's right-hand man is helped by a woman seeking retribution.

tagline: Wish You Were Here
summary: Four college girls hold up a restaurant in order to fund their spring break vacation. While partying, drinking, and taking drugs, they are arrested, only to be bailed out by a drug and arms dealer.

tagline: A journey out of darkness into light
summary: In Persia in the 11th Century, a surgeon's apprentice disguises himself as a Jew to study at a school that does not admit Christians.

tagline: Two strangers. One extraordinary connection.

tagline: No ordinary place. No ordinary crime.
summary: Obsessed with the disappearance of a 12-year-old pregnant girl near a freezing lake in New Zealand, a brave detective will find herself up against small-town secrets and a side of herself that was meticulously kept at bay.

tagline: I warned you not to go out tonight
summary: As he helps a young artist with her upcoming exhibition, the owner of a mannequin shop's deadly, suppressed desires come to the surface.

tagline: Coming in hot.
summary: After getting fired and finding out her husband is cheating, Tammy hits the road with her profane, alcoholic grandmother.
A pair of childhood friends and neighbors fall for each other's sons.

primaryTitle: Dawn of the Planet of the Apes
originalTitle: Dawn of the Planet of the Apes
tagline: One last chance for peace.
summary: A growing nation of genetically evolved apes led by Caesar is threatened by a band of human survivors of the devastating virus unleashed a decade earlier.

tagline: This collection is killer.
summary: When a group of misfits are hired by an unknown third party to burglarize a desolate house and acquire a rare VHS tape, they discover more found footage than they bargained for.

tagline: Prepare to go into the storm.
summary: Storm trackers, thrill-seekers, and everyday townspeople document an unprecedented onslaught of tornadoes touching down in the town of Silverton.

tagline: The lie is spreading.
summary: A teacher lives a lonely life, all the while struggling over his son's custody. His life slowly gets better as he finds love and receives good news from his son, but his new luck is about to be brutally shattered by an innocent little lie.

tagline: A supernatural Close Encounters of the Third Kind.
summary: A sci-fi/thriller story centered on a special-ops team that is dispatched to fight supernatural beings.

tagline: It's Closer Than You Think
summary: It has been five years since the disappearance of Katie and Hunter, and a suburban family witness strange events in their neighborhood when a woman and a mysterious child move in.

tagline: This is not war, it's extinction

summary: A man heading towards Rameshwaram via Chennai express to immerse his late grandfather's ashes unwillingly gets caught amidst goons after helping their boss's daughter and them board the train.

primaryTitle: The 100 Year-Old Man Who Climbed Out the Window and Disappeared
originalTitle: Hundraåringen som klev ut genom fönstret och försvann
tagline: Things are what they are, and whatever will be will be.

tagline: Who will survive?
summary: A young woman grieving the loss of her mother, a famous scream queen from the 1980s, finds herself pulled into the world of her mom's most famous movie. Reunited, the women must fight off the film's maniacal killer.

primaryTitle: The House with a Clock in Its Walls
originalTitle: The House with a Clock in Its Walls
tagline: Magic lives behind every door.
summary: A young orphan named Lewis Barnavelt aids his magical uncle in locating a clock with the power to bring about the end of the world.

tagline: The world needed heroes. They got these guys.
summary: When aliens misinterpret video feeds of classic arcade games as a declaration of war, they attack the Earth in the form of the video games.

tagline: The consequences in the fear and flight situation.
summary: A family vacationing in the French Alps is confronted with a devastating avalanche.

tagline: ¡Sin duda la mejor película del año! [MX]
summary: Faced with both her hot-tempered father's fading health and melting ice-caps that flood her ramshackle bayou community and unleash ancient aurochs, six-year-old Hushpuppy must learn the ways of courage and love.

tagline: He was a star in the making, who vanished without a trace. But on the other side of the world, he inspired a generation.
summary: Two South Africans set out to discover what happened to their unlikely musical hero, the mysterious 1970s rock n roller, Rodriguez.

tagline: Ever have one of THOSE days...? Pray you don't.
summary: In the aftermath of a massive earthquake in California, a rescue-chopper pilot makes a dangerous journey with his ex-wife across the state in order to rescue his daughter.

tagline: Living the Dream, One Heist at a Time
summary: Inspired by actual events, a group of fame-obsessed teenagers use the internet to track celebrities' whereabouts in order to rob their homes.

tagline: Arousing America's curiosity (Season 1)
summary: Drama about the pioneers of the science of human sexuality whose research touched off the sexual revolution.

tagline: Sometimes love just writes itself...
summary: Unrequited love motivates a guy to write about his experiences.

tagline: Unlikely but not impossible.
summary: Journalist Fred Flarsky reunites with his childhood crush, Charlotte Field, now one of the most influential women in the world. As she prepares to make a run for the Presidency, Charlotte hires Fred as her speechwriter and sparks fly.

originalTitle: Ôkami kodomo no Ame to Yuki
tagline: Love wildly
summary: After her werewolf lover unexpectedly dies in an accident while hunting for food for their children, a young woman must find ways to raise the werewolf son and daughter that she had with him while keeping their trait hidden from society.

tagline: Behind the beloved book is a story beyond words.
summary: Author P.L. Travers reflects on her childhood after reluctantly meeting with Walt Disney, who seeks to adapt her Mary Poppins books for the big screen.

tagline: Would you take a life to live forever?
summary: A dying real estate mogul transfers his consciousness into a healthy young body, but soon finds that neither the procedure nor the company that performed it are quite what they seem.
Tanu and Manu's marriage collapses. What happens when Manu meets Tanu's lookalike Kusum - and when Tanu returns?

tagline: Do you like puzzles?
summary: As a math savant uncooks the books for a new client, the Treasury Department closes in on his activities, and the body count starts to rise.

tagline: A love story for their ages
summary: A snowstorm forces two people who made an online connection to unwillingly extend their one-night stand as the blizzard goes through the night.

tagline: All's fair in love and cold war.
summary: At the height of the Cold War two Russian agents pose as your average American couple, complete with family.

tagline: The true story of an incredible adventure from the producers of The King's Speech
summary: A young woman goes on a 1,700-mile trek across the deserts of West Australia with four camels and her faithful dog.

tagline: The end justifies the mean.
summary: A spelling bee loser sets out to exact revenge by finding a loophole and attempting to win as an adult.

tagline: New crime. Same tools.

tagline: With neighbours like these, who needs family?
summary: A young boy whose parents have just divorced finds an unlikely friend and mentor in the misanthropic, bawdy, hedonistic war veteran who lives next door.

tagline: Eventually stars burn out.

tagline: The question is, kill or die?
summary: A dying CIA agent trying to reconnect with his estranged daughter is offered an experimental drug that could save his life in exchange for one last assignment.
A woman is made to realize that her prayers and sacrifice to save her boyfriend's life may have led him to a fate worse than death.

Diana Bishop, historian and witch, accesses Ashmole 782 and knows she must solve its mysteries. She is offered help by the enigmatic Matthew Clairmont, but he's a vampire and witches should never trust vampires.

tagline: It was the greatest art heist in history
summary: An unlikely World War II platoon is tasked to rescue art masterpieces from Nazi thieves and return them to their owners.
Kabir and Naina bond during a trekking trip. Before Naina can express herself, Kabir leaves India to pursue his career. They meet again years later, but he still cherishes his dreams more than bonds.

tagline: Discover a world you never knew expected.
summary: Three teenage friends, in the ultimate act of independence, decide to spend their summer building a house in the woods and living off the land.

tagline: 150 kills made history
summary: Navy S.E.A.L. sniper Chris Kyle's pinpoint accuracy saves countless lives on the battlefield and turns him into a legend. Back home with his family after four tours of duty, however, Chris finds that it is the war he can't leave behind.

tagline: Be careful what you wish for
summary: A witch tasks a childless baker and his wife with procuring magical items from classic fairy tales to reverse the curse put on their family tree.
A quiet, sweet tempered housewife endures small slights from her well-educated husband and daughter every day because of her inability to speak and understand English.

tagline: Survive the night.
summary: A wealthy family is held hostage for harboring the target of a murderous syndicate during the Purge, a 12-hour period in which any and all crime is legal.

tagline: Blood is thicker. (Season 2)
summary: A contemporary prequel to Psycho, giving a portrayal of how Norman Bates' psyche unravels through his teenage years, and how deeply intricate his relationship with his mother, Norma, truly is.

tagline: Everyone has a breaking point. (season 2)
summary: Life in the city of Defiance, in a near future after the arrival of different alien lifeforms to Earth.

tagline: Worlds will collide (Season 1)
summary: In a world replete with greed, betrayal, sexual intrigue and rivalry, "Marco Polo" is based on the famed explorer's adventures in Kublai Khan's court in 13th century Mongolia.

tagline: Perfect crimes meet the perfect match. (season 3)
summary: A modern take on the cases of Sherlock Holmes, with the detective now living in New York City.

tagline: A few years ago, some old friends shared one unforgettable weekend.
summary: After moving his family back to his hometown to be with his friends and their kids, Lenny finds out that between old bullies, new bullies, schizo bus drivers, drunk cops on skis, and four hundred costumed party crashers sometimes crazy follows you.

tagline: Those closest to you can hurt you the most. (season 3)
summary: Spoiled billionaire playboy Oliver Queen is missing and presumed dead when his yacht is lost at sea. He returns five years later a changed man, determined to clean up the city as a hooded vigilante armed with a bow.

tagline: How brave is your love?
summary: A beautiful detective falls in love with an ex-soldier who goes into hiding from the secret government organization that turned him into a mechanically charged beast.

tagline: Sin Is A Choice.
summary: A lawyer finds himself in over his head when he gets involved in drug trafficking.

tagline: What if every moment in life came with a second chance?
summary: At the age of 21, Tim discovers he can travel in time and change what happens and has happened in his own life. His decision to make his world a better place by getting a girlfriend turns out not to be as easy as you might think.

When a classical dancer's suspecting wife sets an investigator behind him, a series of violent events are triggered, revealing his real identity and connection to a darker world.

tagline: Love Makes Life Live...
summary: Rahul loses his fans and fame due to alcoholism. But he then decides to turn a small time singer into a rising star.

tagline: He'll never know what hit him.
summary: After discovering her boyfriend is married, Carly soon meets the wife he's been betraying. And when yet another love affair is discovered, all three women team up to plot revenge on the three-timing S.O.B.

tagline: A story of first loves and second chances.
summary: An acclaimed writer, his ex-wife, and their teenaged children come to terms with the complexities of love in all its forms over the course of one tumultuous year.

tagline: Everything's better with maturity
summary: We meet Jesse and Celine nine years on in Greece. Almost two decades have passed since their first meeting on that train bound for Vienna.

tagline: They had a plan to save mankind, until one moment changed everything.
summary: A scientist's drive for artificial intelligence takes on dangerous implications when his own consciousness is uploaded into one such program.

tagline: For everyone whose life is a work in progress. (Season 1)
summary: A young Ob/Gyn doctor balances her personal and professional life, surrounded by quirky co-workers in a small office.

tagline: It's never too easy to achieve something valuable.
summary: Three friends growing up in India at the turn of the millennium set out to open a training academy to produce the country's next cricket stars.
In a monster-infested world, Joel learns his girlfriend is just 85 miles away. To make the dangerous journey, Joel discovers his inner hero to be with the girl of his dreams.

summary: At the NFL Draft, General Manager Sonny Weaver has the opportunity to rebuild his team when he trades for the number one pick. He must decide what he's willing to sacrifice on a life-changing day for a few hundred young men with NFL dreams.

tagline: Worlds Collide
summary: An alien on the run from his own people makes friends with a girl. He tries to help her on her quest, but can be an interference.

tagline: It will take what you love most.

tagline: What if your life depended on a stranger?
summary: Stranded after a tragic plane crash, two strangers must forge a connection to survive the extreme elements of a remote snow-covered mountain. When they realize help is not coming, they embark on a perilous journey across the wilderness.

tagline: Everyone loves a happy ending
summary: A New Jersey guy dedicated to his family, friends, and church, develops unrealistic expectations from watching porn and works to find happiness and intimacy with his potential true love.

tagline: Be afraid. Be effing afraid.
summary: After her mother's mysterious death, Nica begins to suspect that the talking, red-haired doll her visiting niece has been playing with may be the key to recent bloodshed and chaos.

tagline: Never bet against a man with a killer hand
summary: When a Las Vegas bodyguard with lethal skills and a gambling problem gets in trouble with the mob, he has one last play...and it's all or nothing.

tagline: Big Meets Bigger
summary: When three different animals become infected with a dangerous pathogen, a primatologist and a geneticist team up to stop them from destroying Chicago.

tagline: Killing a priest on a Sunday. That'll be a good one.
summary: After he is threatened during a confession, a good-natured priest must battle the dark forces closing in around him.

tagline: Hiring them was a brilliant mistake.
summary: Two salesmen whose careers have been torpedoed by the digital age find their way into a coveted internship at Google, where they must compete with a group of young, tech-savvy geniuses for a shot at employment.

tagline: I am not your property. (season 3)
summary: A streetwise hustler is pulled into a compelling conspiracy after witnessing the suicide of a girl who looks just like her.

A young newlywed arrives at her husband's imposing family estate on a windswept English coast and finds herself battling the shadow of his first wife, Rebecca, whose legacy lives on in the house long after her death.

tagline: I was 17 when my mother disappeared...
summary: In 1988, a teenage girl's life is thrown into chaos when her mother disappears.

primaryTitle: Valerian and the City of a Thousand Planets
originalTitle: Valerian and the City of a Thousand Planets
tagline: A universe without boundaries needs heroes without limits.
summary: A dark force threatens Alpha, a vast metropolis and home to species from a thousand planets. Special operatives Valerian and Laureline must race to identify the marauding menace and safeguard not just Alpha, but the future of the universe.

tagline: On the air. Out of time.
summary: Financial TV host Lee Gates and his producer Patty are put in an extreme situation when an irate investor takes them and their crew as hostage.

tagline: This $*%! ain't paranormal!
summary: Malcolm and Kisha move into their dream home, but soon learn a demon also resides there. When Kisha becomes possessed, Malcolm - determined to keep his sex life on track - turns to a priest, a psychic, and a team of ghost-busters for help.

tagline: Feed your fear
summary: Explores the early relationship between renowned psychiatrist, Hannibal Lecter, and his patient, a young FBI criminal profiler, who is haunted by his ability to empathize with serial killers.

Newlywed couple Nat and Josh are deliriously happy despite their differences, though friends and family aren't convinced that they can last. With their first anniversary approaching and attractive alternatives in the mix, can they last?

tagline: From the creators of Wreck-It Ralph and Frozen.
summary: A special bond develops between plus-sized inflatable robot Baymax and prodigy Hiro Hamada, who together team up with a group of friends to form a band of high-tech heroes.

tagline: Save yourself (Season 4)
summary: Ray Donovan, a professional "fixer" for the rich and famous in Los Angeles, can make anyone's problems disappear except those created by his own family.

tagline: Get ready for the stunning final act of this trilogy masterpiece... (season 3)
summary: The murder of a young boy in a small coastal town brings a media frenzy, which threatens to tear the community apart.
In the year 2022, thousands of people get trapped in a new virtual MMORPG and the lone wolf player, Kirito, works to escape.

tagline: Homework can wait. The city can't.
summary: Peter Parker balances his life as an ordinary high school student in Queens with his superhero alter-ego Spider-Man, and finds himself on the trail of a new menace prowling the skies of New York City.

tagline: No body forgets.
summary: Set in a future where consciousness is digitized and stored, a prisoner returns to life in a new body and must solve a mind-bending murder to win his freedom.

tagline: Brave the deep. Find the gold. Trust no one.
summary: In order to make good with his former employers, a submarine captain takes a job with a shadowy backer to search the depths of the Black Sea for a submarine rumored to be loaded with gold.

tagline: A family of Heroes.
summary: The story of firefighters in Chicago, both on a personal and professional level

Manolo, a young man who is torn between fulfilling the expectations of his family and following his heart, embarks on an adventure that spans three fantastic worlds where he must face his greatest fears.

primaryTitle: Dragon Ball Z: Battle of Gods
originalTitle: Dragon Ball Z: Doragon bôru Z - Kami to Kami
tagline: The mightiest make their move
summary: The Z-Fighters must contend with Lord Beerus, the God of Destruction, but only a God can fight a God, and none of them are Gods. However with the creation of the Super Saiyan God, will the Z-Fighters be able to defeat Lord Beerus?

tagline: It's Not Over Yet
summary: Only a short time after the first raid, Rama goes undercover with the thugs of Jakarta and plans to bring down the syndicate and uncover the corruption within his police force.

tagline: A comedy about knowing when to say when.
summary: Luke and Kate are coworkers at a brewery who spend their nights drinking and flirting heavily. One weekend away together with their significant others proves who really belongs together and who doesn't.

tagline: Grab destiny by the rice dumplings.
summary: Continuing his "legendary adventures of awesomeness", Po must face two hugely epic, but different threats: one supernatural and the other a little closer to home.

tagline: From the Director of Se7en and Zodiac
summary: With his wife's disappearance having become the focus of an intense media circus, a man sees the spotlight turned on him when it's suspected that he may not be innocent.

tagline: Back to the grind.
summary: Three years after Mike bowed out of the stripper life at the top of his game, he and the remaining Kings of Tampa hit the road to Myrtle Beach to put on one last blow-out performance.

tagline: Some stories are beyond belief
summary: When disgraced New York Times reporter Michael Finkel meets accused killer Christian Longo - who has taken on Finkel's identity - his investigation morphs into a game of cat-and-mouse.

tagline: Darkness calls.
summary: Based on the graphic novels by Mike Mignola, Hellboy, caught between the worlds of the supernatural and human, battles an ancient sorceress bent on revenge.
Three friends try to make money and invite another friend in on a plot.

tagline: She just kept swimming...
summary: Friendly but forgetful blue tang Dory begins a search for her long-lost parents, and everyone learns a few things about the real meaning of family along the way.
A writer encounters the owner of an aging high-class hotel, who tells him of his early years serving as a lobby boy in the hotel's glorious years under an exceptional concierge.

tagline: Blazingly emotional and explosively sexy.
summary: Adèle's life is changed when she meets Emma, a young woman with blue hair, who will allow her to discover desire and to assert herself as a woman and as an adult. In front of others, Adèle grows, seeks herself, loses herself, and ultimately finds herself through love and loss.

primaryTitle: The SpongeBob Movie: Sponge Out of Water
originalTitle: The SpongeBob Movie: Sponge Out of Water
tagline: A New Adventure, the same boy, I mean hero
summary: When a diabolical pirate above the sea steals the secret Krabby Patty formula, SpongeBob and his nemesis Plankton must team up in order to get it back.

tagline: 2 Frogs 1 Pig Epic Mayhem
summary: While on a grand world tour, The Muppets find themselves wrapped into an European jewel-heist caper headed by a Kermit the Frog look-alike and his dastardly sidekick.

tagline: The world's not going to save itself
summary: The Men in Black have always protected the Earth from the scum of the universe. In this new adventure, they tackle their biggest threat to date: a mole in the Men in Black organization.

tagline: Landing This Christmas.
summary: Four teenagers are sucked into a magical video game, and the only way they can escape is to work together to finish the game.

tagline: Kanjibhai is taking God to court!
summary: A shopkeeper takes God to court when his shop is destroyed by an earthquake.

tagline: Uh oh.
summary: Minions Stuart, Kevin, and Bob are recruited by Scarlet Overkill, a supervillain who, alongside her inventor husband Herb, hatches a plot to take over the world.

tagline: A race against time between 2 hunters on opposite sides of the law. (season 1)
summary: A seemingly cold but very passionate policewoman goes head to head with a seemingly passionate father who is in fact a cold serial killer in this procedural out of Belfast. The only thing they share is their common complexity.

tagline: They're not 21 anymore
summary: After making their way through high school (twice), big changes are in store for officers Schmidt and Jenko when they go deep undercover at a local college.

When the newly crowned Queen Elsa accidentally uses her power to turn things into ice to curse her home in infinite winter, her sister Anna teams up with a mountain man, his playful reindeer, and a snowman to change the weather condition.

tagline: Speak up and let your voice be heard.
summary: An underachieving voice coach finds herself competing in the movie trailer voice-over profession against her arrogant father and his protégé.

tagline: The legend takes new life.
summary: Dracula travels to London, with dark plans for revenge against those who ruined his life centuries earlier. However, his plan is complicated when he falls in love with a woman who seems to be a reincarnation of his dead wife.

tagline: We are never stronger than when we are tested.
summary: Secret Service agent Mike Banning finds himself trapped inside the White House in the wake of a terrorist attack and works with national security to rescue the President from his kidnappers.
Drama series following the investigations of AC-12, a controversial police anticorruption unit.

tagline: It is an ideal for which I am prepared to die.
summary: A chronicle of Nelson Mandela's life journey from his childhood in a rural village through to his inauguration as the first democratically elected president of South Africa.

tagline: We fight back.
summary: Four waves of increasingly deadly alien attacks have left most of Earth in ruin. Cassie is on the run, desperately trying to save her younger brother.

tagline: Based on the inspirational best seller.
summary: A chronicle of one woman's one thousand one hundred mile solo hike undertaken as a way to recover from a recent personal tragedy.

tagline: The Storm Is Coming
summary: Vikings transports us to the brutal and mysterious world of Ragnar Lothbrok, a Viking warrior and farmer who yearns to explore - and raid - the distant shores across the ocean.

tagline: The monster is within.
summary: Secrets are just part of daily life in the small Pennsylvania town of Hemlock Grove, where the darkest evils hide in plain sight.

primaryTitle: The Hobbit: The Battle of the Five Armies
originalTitle: The Hobbit: The Battle of the Five Armies
tagline: The epic conclusion to 'The Hobbit' trilogy.
summary: Bilbo and company are forced to engage in a war against an array of combatants and keep the Lonely Mountain from falling into the hands of a rising darkness.

tagline: How far would you go to protect your home?
summary: A former DEA agent moves his family to a quiet town, where he soon tangles with a local meth druglord.

tagline: Witness the Creation of Fear.
summary: The crew of a colony ship, bound for a remote planet, discover an uncharted paradise with a threat beyond their imagination, and must attempt a harrowing escape.

tagline: From the Director of Prisoners
summary: A man seeks out his exact look-alike after spotting him in a movie.

tagline: They rise. We fall.
summary: In efforts to construct perfect android killing machines in a war against China, UK scientists exceed their goal and create a sentient robot.
A man is brought in by an infertility doctor to supply him with his sperm, where he becomes the biggest sperm donor for his clinic.

tagline: When you fall for the right person, at the right time, for all the right reasons, what can possibly go wrong...?
summary: The story of a privileged girl and a charismatic boy whose instant desire sparks a love affair made only more reckless by parents trying to keep them apart.

tagline: Don't let it in.
summary: A single mother and her child fall into a deep well of paranoia when an eerie children's book titled "Mister Babadook" manifests in their home.

tagline: The worldwide phenomenon comes to life.
summary: Literature student Anastasia Steele's life changes forever when she meets handsome, yet tormented, billionaire Christian Grey.

primaryTitle: A Girl Walks Home Alone at Night
originalTitle: A Girl Walks Home Alone at Night
tagline: The first Iranian Vampire Western
summary: In the Iranian ghost-town Bad City, a place that reeks of death and loneliness, the townspeople are unaware they are being stalked by a lonesome vampire.

tagline: When hope is all you have.
summary: Eight years after the disappearance of Cassandra, some disturbing incidents seem to indicate that she's still alive. Police, parents and Cassandra herself, will try to unravel the mystery of her disappearance.

tagline: Born to Fight

tagline: New team. New attitude. New mission.
summary: Barney augments his team with new blood for a personal battle: to take down Conrad Stonebanks, the Expendables co-founder and notorious arms trader who is hell bent on wiping out Barney and every single one of his associates.

tagline: Nothing is everything.
summary: A hugely talented but socially isolated computer operator is tasked by Management to prove the Zero Theorem: that the universe ends as nothing, rendering life meaningless. But meaning is what he already craves.

tagline: Every step brings you closer to the edge.
summary: The story of Oscar Grant III, a 22-year-old Bay Area resident, who crosses paths with friends, enemies, family, and strangers on the last day of 2008.

tagline: Mess with me, mess with my mother.
summary: When her boyfriend dumps her before their exotic vacation, a young woman persuades her ultra-cautious mother to travel with her to paradise, with unexpected results.
A New York socialite, deeply troubled and in denial, arrives in San Francisco to impose upon her sister. She looks a million, but isn't bringing money, peace, or love...

tagline: It Will Start Like Any Other Day.
summary: While on a tour of the White House with his young daughter, a Capitol policeman springs into action to save his child and protect the president from a heavily armed group of paramilitary invaders.
An alien on Earth loses the only device he can use to communicate with his spaceship. His innocent nature and child-like questions force the country to evaluate the impact of religion on its people.

primaryTitle: The Woman in Black 2: Angel of Death
originalTitle: The Woman in Black 2: Angel of Death
tagline: She Never Left.
summary: 40 years after the first haunting at Eel Marsh House, a group of children evacuated from WWII London arrives, awakening the house's darkest inhabitant.

tagline: Watch Me.
summary: Three interlocking love stories involving three couples in three cities: Rome, Paris, and New York.

tagline: Things fall apart. The center cannot hold. Anarchy is loosed upon the world.

tagline: Welcome to a New World of Gods and Monsters
summary: An ancient Egyptian princess is awakened from her crypt beneath the desert, bringing with her malevolence grown over millennia, and terrors that defy human comprehension.

tagline: India's lunchbox delivery system transports thousands of meals every day from kitchens to offices.

tagline: Now you will see his Real Story.
summary: The truth behind the ascension of Milkha Singh who was scarred because of the India-Pakistan partition.

tagline: We get the world we deserve. (Season 2)
summary: Seasonal anthology series in which police investigations unearth the personal and professional secrets of those involved, both within and outside the law.

tagline: Some see what's possible, others change what's possible.

tagline: Hell's Kitchen Has A New Hero (season 1)
summary: Following the tragic end of her brief superhero career, Jessica Jones tries to rebuild her life as a private investigator, dealing with cases involving people with remarkable abilities in New York City.

Jep Gambardella has seduced his way through the lavish nightlife of Rome for decades, but after his 65th birthday and a shock from the past, Jep looks past the nightclubs and parties to find a timeless landscape of absurd, exquisite beauty.

tagline: Work hard, play harder!
summary: A hard-working small business owner and his two associates travel to Europe to close the most important deal of their lives. But what began as a routine business trip goes off the rails in every way imaginable, and unimaginable.

tagline: A Man With Nothing To Lose Is A Man With Nothing To Fear.
summary: A mysterious outsider's quiet life is turned upside down when he returns to his childhood home to carry out an act of vengeance. Proving himself an amateur assassin, he winds up in a brutal fight to protect his estranged family.
Kundan, the son of a Hindu pundit, discovers that his childhood sweetheart Zoya loves city-bred Akram and wants to marry him. However, he persistently seeks to win her heart.

tagline: Witness the price of the American Dream.
summary: A group of Boston-bred gangsters set up shop in balmy Florida during the Prohibition era, facing off against the competition and the Ku Klux Klan.

tagline: Experience never gets old.
summary: Seventy-year-old widower Ben Whittaker has discovered that retirement isn't all it's cracked up to be. Seizing an opportunity to get back in the game, he becomes a senior intern at an online fashion site, founded and run by Jules Ostin.

tagline: Are you inhuman? (season 3)
summary: The missions of the Strategic Homeland Intervention, Enforcement and Logistics Division.

tagline: Know when to walk away.
summary: When a poor college student who cracks an online poker game goes bust, he arranges a face-to-face with the man he thinks cheated him, a sly offshore entrepreneur.

tagline: With law comes disorder.
summary: A young pickpocket and an unruly CIA agent team up on an anti-terrorist mission in France.
